2385/* Put ALLOCNO onto the coloring stack and remove it from its bucket.
2386 The allocno is in the colorable bucket if COLORABLE_P is TRUE. */
2387static void
2388remove_allocno_from_bucket_and_push (ira_allocno_t allocno, bool colorable_p)
2389{
2390 if (colorable_p)
2391 delete_allocno_from_bucket (allocno, &colorable_allocno_bucket);
2392 else
2393 delete_allocno_from_bucket (allocno, &uncolorable_allocno_bucket);
2394 if (internal_flag_ira_verbose > 3 && ira_dump_file != NULL)
2395 {
2396 fprintf (ira_dump_file, " Pushing");
2397 ira_print_expanded_allocno (allocno);
2398 if (colorable_p)
2399 fprintf (ira_dump_file, "(cost %d)\n",
2400 ALLOCNO_COLOR_DATA (allocno)->temp);
2401 else
2402 fprintf (ira_dump_file, "(potential spill: %spri=%d, cost=%d)\n",
2403 ALLOCNO_BAD_SPILL_P (allocno) ? "bad spill, " : "",
2404 allocno_spill_priority (allocno),
2405 ALLOCNO_COLOR_DATA (allocno)->temp);
2406 }
2407 if (! colorable_p)
2408 ALLOCNO_COLOR_DATA (allocno)->may_be_spilled_p = true;
2409 push_allocno_to_stack (allocno);
2410}
2411
2412/* Put all allocnos from colorable bucket onto the coloring stack. */
2413static void
2414push_only_colorable (void)
2415{
2416 form_threads_from_bucket (colorable_allocno_bucket);
2417 sort_bucket (&colorable_allocno_bucket, bucket_allocno_compare_func);
2418 for (;colorable_allocno_bucket != NULL;)
2419 remove_allocno_from_bucket_and_push (colorable_allocno_bucket, true);
2420}
2421
2422/* Return the frequency of exit edges (if EXIT_P) or entry from/to the
2423 loop given by its LOOP_NODE. */
2424int
2425ira_loop_edge_freq (ira_loop_tree_node_t loop_node, int regno, bool exit_p)
2426{
2427 int freq, i;
2428 edge_iterator ei;
2429 edge e;
2430 vec<edge> edges;
2431
2432 ira_assert (current_loops != NULL && loop_node->loop != NULL
2433 && (regno < 0 || regno >= FIRST_PSEUDO_REGISTER));
2434 freq = 0;
2435 if (! exit_p)
2436 {
2437 FOR_EACH_EDGE (e, ei, loop_node->loop->header->preds)
2438 if (e->src != loop_node->loop->latch
2439 && (regno < 0
2440 || (bitmap_bit_p (df_get_live_out (e->src), regno)
2441 && bitmap_bit_p (df_get_live_in (e->dest), regno))))
2442 freq += EDGE_FREQUENCY (e);
2443 }
2444 else
2445 {
2446 edges = get_loop_exit_edges (loop_node->loop);
2447 FOR_EACH_VEC_ELT (edges, i, e)
2448 if (regno < 0
2449 || (bitmap_bit_p (df_get_live_out (e->src), regno)
2450 && bitmap_bit_p (df_get_live_in (e->dest), regno)))
2451 freq += EDGE_FREQUENCY (e);
2452 edges.release ();
2453 }
2454
2455 return REG_FREQ_FROM_EDGE_FREQ (freq);
2456}
2457
2458/* Calculate and return the cost of putting allocno A into memory. */
2459static int
2460calculate_allocno_spill_cost (ira_allocno_t a)
2461{
2462 int regno, cost;
2463 machine_mode mode;
2464 enum reg_class rclass;
2465 ira_allocno_t parent_allocno;
2466 ira_loop_tree_node_t parent_node, loop_node;
2467
2468 regno = ALLOCNO_REGNO (a);
2469 cost = ALLOCNO_UPDATED_MEMORY_COST (a) - ALLOCNO_UPDATED_CLASS_COST (a);
2470 if (ALLOCNO_CAP (a) != NULL)
2471 return cost;
2472 loop_node = ALLOCNO_LOOP_TREE_NODE (a);
2473 if ((parent_node = loop_node->parent) == NULL)
2474 return cost;
2475 if ((parent_allocno = parent_node->regno_allocno_map[regno]) == NULL)
2476 return cost;
2477 mode = ALLOCNO_MODE (a);
2478 rclass = ALLOCNO_CLASS (a);
2479 if (ALLOCNO_HARD_REGNO (parent_allocno) < 0)
2480 cost -= (ira_memory_move_cost[mode][rclass][0]
2481 * ira_loop_edge_freq (loop_node, regno, true)
2482 + ira_memory_move_cost[mode][rclass][1]
2483 * ira_loop_edge_freq (loop_node, regno, false));
2484 else
2485 {
2486 ira_init_register_move_cost_if_necessary (mode);
2487 cost += ((ira_memory_move_cost[mode][rclass][1]
2488 * ira_loop_edge_freq (loop_node, regno, true)
2489 + ira_memory_move_cost[mode][rclass][0]
2490 * ira_loop_edge_freq (loop_node, regno, false))
2491 - (ira_register_move_cost[mode][rclass][rclass]
2492 * (ira_loop_edge_freq (loop_node, regno, false)
2493 + ira_loop_edge_freq (loop_node, regno, true))));
2494 }
2495 return cost;
2496}
2497
2498/* Used for sorting allocnos for spilling. */
2499static inline int
2500allocno_spill_priority_compare (ira_allocno_t a1, ira_allocno_t a2)
2501{
2502 int pri1, pri2, diff;
2503
2504 /* Avoid spilling static chain pointer pseudo when non-local goto is
2505 used. */
2506 if (non_spilled_static_chain_regno_p (ALLOCNO_REGNO (a1)))
2507 return 1;
2508 else if (non_spilled_static_chain_regno_p (ALLOCNO_REGNO (a2)))
2509 return -1;
2510 if (ALLOCNO_BAD_SPILL_P (a1) && ! ALLOCNO_BAD_SPILL_P (a2))
2511 return 1;
2512 if (ALLOCNO_BAD_SPILL_P (a2) && ! ALLOCNO_BAD_SPILL_P (a1))
2513 return -1;
2514 pri1 = allocno_spill_priority (a1);
2515 pri2 = allocno_spill_priority (a2);
2516 if ((diff = pri1 - pri2) != 0)
2517 return diff;
2518 if ((diff
2519 = ALLOCNO_COLOR_DATA (a1)->temp - ALLOCNO_COLOR_DATA (a2)->temp) != 0)
2520 return diff;
2521 return ALLOCNO_NUM (a1) - ALLOCNO_NUM (a2);
2522}
2523
2524/* Used for sorting allocnos for spilling. */
2525static int
2526allocno_spill_sort_compare (const void *v1p, const void *v2p)
2527{
2528 ira_allocno_t p1 = *(const ira_allocno_t *) v1p;
2529 ira_allocno_t p2 = *(const ira_allocno_t *) v2p;
2530
2531 return allocno_spill_priority_compare (p1, p2);
2532}

2534/* Push allocnos to the coloring stack. The order of allocnos in the
2535 stack defines the order for the subsequent coloring. */
2536static void
2537push_allocnos_to_stack (void)
2538{
2539 ira_allocno_t a;
2540 int cost;
2541
2542 /* Calculate uncolorable allocno spill costs. */
2543 for (a = uncolorable_allocno_bucket;
2544 a != NULL;
2545 a = ALLOCNO_COLOR_DATA (a)->next_bucket_allocno)
2546 if (ALLOCNO_CLASS (a) != NO_REGS)
2547 {
2548 cost = calculate_allocno_spill_cost (a);
2549 /* ??? Remove cost of copies between the coalesced
2550 allocnos. */
2551 ALLOCNO_COLOR_DATA (a)->temp = cost;
2552 }
2553 sort_bucket (&uncolorable_allocno_bucket, allocno_spill_sort_compare);
2554 for (;;)
2555 {
2556 push_only_colorable ();
2557 a = uncolorable_allocno_bucket;
2558 if (a == NULL)
2559 break;
2560 remove_allocno_from_bucket_and_push (a, false);
2561 }
2562 ira_assert (colorable_allocno_bucket == NULL
2563 && uncolorable_allocno_bucket == NULL);
2564 ira_assert (uncolorable_allocnos_num == 0);
2565}

2570pop_allocnos_from_stack (void)
2571{

2573 enum reg_class aclass;
2574
2575 for (;allocno_stack_vec.length () != 0;)
2576 {

2578 aclass = ALLOCNO_CLASS (allocno);
2579 if (internal_flag_ira_verbose > 3 && ira_dump_file != NULL)
2580 {
2581 fprintf (ira_dump_file, " Popping");
2582 ira_print_expanded_allocno (allocno);
2583 fprintf (ira_dump_file, " -- ");
2584 }
2585 if (aclass == NO_REGS)
2586 {
2587 ALLOCNO_HARD_REGNO (allocno) = -1;
2588 ALLOCNO_ASSIGNED_P (allocno) = true;
2589 ira_assert (ALLOCNO_UPDATED_HARD_REG_COSTS (allocno) == NULL);

2591 (ALLOCNO_UPDATED_CONFLICT_HARD_REG_COSTS (allocno) == NULL);
2592 if (internal_flag_ira_verbose > 3 && ira_dump_file != NULL)
2593 fprintf (ira_dump_file, "assign memory\n");
2594 }
2595 else if (assign_hard_reg (allocno, false))
2596 {
2597 if (internal_flag_ira_verbose > 3 && ira_dump_file != NULL)
2598 fprintf (ira_dump_file, "assign reg %d\n",
2599 ALLOCNO_HARD_REGNO (allocno));
2600 }
2601 else if (ALLOCNO_ASSIGNED_P (allocno))
2602 {
2603 if (internal_flag_ira_verbose > 3 && ira_dump_file != NULL)
2604 fprintf (ira_dump_file, "spill%s\n",
2605 ALLOCNO_COLOR_DATA (allocno)->may_be_spilled_p
2606 ? "" : "!");
2607 }
2608 ALLOCNO_COLOR_DATA (allocno)->in_graph_p = true;
2609 }

2641 reg_class_names[aclass], ira_class_hard_regs_num[aclass], n);

2648 data->hard_regs_node->hard_regs->set, false);
2649 for (i = 0; i < nwords; i++)
2650 {
2651 ira_object_t obj = ALLOCNO_OBJECT (a, i);

2660 print_hard_reg_set (ira_dump_file, OBJECT_TOTAL_CONFLICT_HARD_REGS (obj),

2667/* Put ALLOCNO in a bucket corresponding to its number and size of its
2668 conflicting allocnos and hard registers. */
2669static void
2670put_allocno_into_bucket (ira_allocno_t allocno)
2671{

2679
2680/* Map: allocno number -> allocno priority. */
2681static int *allocno_priorities;
2682
2683/* Set up priorities for N allocnos in array
2684 CONSIDERATION_ALLOCNOS. */
2685static void
2686setup_allocno_priorities (ira_allocno_t *consideration_allocnos, int n)
2687{
2688 int i, length, nrefs, priority, max_priority, mult;
2689 ira_allocno_t a;
2690
2691 max_priority = 0;
2692 for (i = 0; i < n; i++)
2693 {
2694 a = consideration_allocnos[i];
2695 nrefs = ALLOCNO_NREFS (a);
2696 ira_assert (nrefs >= 0);
2697 mult = floor_log2 (ALLOCNO_NREFS (a)) + 1;
2698 ira_assert (mult >= 0);
2699 allocno_priorities[ALLOCNO_NUM (a)]
2700 = priority
2701 = (mult
2702 * (ALLOCNO_MEMORY_COST (a) - ALLOCNO_CLASS_COST (a))
2703 * ira_reg_class_max_nregs[ALLOCNO_CLASS (a)][ALLOCNO_MODE (a)]);
2704 if (priority < 0)
2705 priority = -priority;
2706 if (max_priority < priority)
2707 max_priority = priority;
2708 }
2709 mult = max_priority == 0 ? 1 : INT_MAX / max_priority;
2710 for (i = 0; i < n; i++)
2711 {
2712 a = consideration_allocnos[i];
2713 length = ALLOCNO_EXCESS_PRESSURE_POINTS_NUM (a);
2714 if (ALLOCNO_NUM_OBJECTS (a) > 1)
2715 length /= ALLOCNO_NUM_OBJECTS (a);
2716 if (length <= 0)
2717 length = 1;
2718 allocno_priorities[ALLOCNO_NUM (a)]
2719 = allocno_priorities[ALLOCNO_NUM (a)] * mult / length;
2720 }
2721}
2722
2723/* Sort allocnos according to the profit of usage of a hard register
2724 instead of memory for them. */
2725static int
2726allocno_cost_compare_func (const void *v1p, const void *v2p)
2727{
2728 ira_allocno_t p1 = *(const ira_allocno_t *) v1p;
2729 ira_allocno_t p2 = *(const ira_allocno_t *) v2p;
2730 int c1, c2;
2731
2732 c1 = ALLOCNO_UPDATED_MEMORY_COST (p1) - ALLOCNO_UPDATED_CLASS_COST (p1);
2733 c2 = ALLOCNO_UPDATED_MEMORY_COST (p2) - ALLOCNO_UPDATED_CLASS_COST (p2);
2734 if (c1 - c2)
2735 return c1 - c2;
2736
2737 /* If regs are equally good, sort by allocno numbers, so that the
2738 results of qsort leave nothing to chance. */
2739 return ALLOCNO_NUM (p1) - ALLOCNO_NUM (p2);
2740}
2741
2742/* Return savings on removed copies when ALLOCNO is assigned to
2743 HARD_REGNO. */
2744static int
2745allocno_copy_cost_saving (ira_allocno_t allocno, int hard_regno)
2746{
2747 int cost = 0;
2748 enum machine_mode allocno_mode = ALLOCNO_MODE (allocno);
2749 enum reg_class rclass;
2750 ira_copy_t cp, next_cp;
2751
2752 rclass = REGNO_REG_CLASS (hard_regno);
2753 if (ira_reg_class_max_nregs[rclass][allocno_mode]
2754 > ira_class_hard_regs_num[rclass])
2755 /* For the above condition the cost can be wrong. Use the allocno
2756 class in this case. */
2757 rclass = ALLOCNO_CLASS (allocno);
2758 for (cp = ALLOCNO_COPIES (allocno); cp != NULL; cp = next_cp)
2759 {
2760 if (cp->first == allocno)
2761 {
2762 next_cp = cp->next_first_allocno_copy;
2763 if (ALLOCNO_HARD_REGNO (cp->second) != hard_regno)
2764 continue;
2765 }
2766 else if (cp->second == allocno)
2767 {
2768 next_cp = cp->next_second_allocno_copy;
2769 if (ALLOCNO_HARD_REGNO (cp->first) != hard_regno)
2770 continue;
2771 }
2772 else
2773 gcc_unreachable ();
2774 cost += cp->freq *
2775 ( ira_register_move_cost
2776 && ira_register_move_cost[allocno_mode]
2777 && ira_register_move_cost[allocno_mode][rclass]
2778 )
2779 ? ira_register_move_cost[allocno_mode][rclass][rclass]
2780 : 0;
2781 }
2782 return cost;
2783}
2784
2785/* We used Chaitin-Briggs coloring to assign as many pseudos as
2786 possible to hard registers. Let us try to improve allocation with
2787 cost point of view. This function improves the allocation by
2788 spilling some allocnos and assigning the freed hard registers to
2789 other allocnos if it decreases the overall allocation cost. */
2790static void
2791improve_allocation (void)
2792{
2793 unsigned int i;
2794 int j, k, n, hregno, conflict_hregno, base_cost, class_size, word, nwords;
2795 int check, spill_cost, min_cost, nregs, conflict_nregs, r, best;
2796 bool try_p;
2797 enum reg_class aclass;
2798 machine_mode mode;
2799 int *allocno_costs;
2800 int costs[FIRST_PSEUDO_REGISTER];
2801 HARD_REG_SET conflicting_regs[2], profitable_hard_regs;
2802 ira_allocno_t a;
2803 bitmap_iterator bi;
2804
2805 /* Don't bother to optimize the code with static chain pointer and
2806 non-local goto in order not to spill the chain pointer
2807 pseudo. */
2808 if (cfun->static_chain_decl && crtl->has_nonlocal_goto)
2809 return;
2810 /* Clear counts used to process conflicting allocnos only once for
2811 each allocno. */
2812 EXECUTE_IF_SET_IN_BITMAP (coloring_allocno_bitmap, 0, i, bi)
2813 ALLOCNO_COLOR_DATA (ira_allocnos[i])->temp = 0;
2814 check = n = 0;
2815 /* Process each allocno and try to assign a hard register to it by
2816 spilling some its conflicting allocnos. */
2817 EXECUTE_IF_SET_IN_BITMAP (coloring_allocno_bitmap, 0, i, bi)
2818 {
2819 a = ira_allocnos[i];
2820 ALLOCNO_COLOR_DATA (a)->temp = 0;
2821 if (empty_profitable_hard_regs (a))
2822 continue;
2823 check++;
2824 aclass = ALLOCNO_CLASS (a);
2825 allocno_costs = ALLOCNO_HARD_REG_COSTS (a);
2826 if ((hregno = ALLOCNO_HARD_REGNO (a)) < 0)
2827 base_cost = ALLOCNO_UPDATED_MEMORY_COST (a);
2828 else if (allocno_costs == NULL)
2829 /* It means that assigning a hard register is not profitable
2830 (we don't waste memory for hard register costs in this
2831 case). */
2832 continue;
2833 else
2834 base_cost = (allocno_costs[ira_class_hard_reg_index[aclass][hregno]]
2835 - allocno_copy_cost_saving (a, hregno));
2836 try_p = false;
2837 get_conflict_and_start_profitable_regs (a, false,
2838 conflicting_regs,
2839 &profitable_hard_regs);
2840 class_size = ira_class_hard_regs_num[aclass];
2841 /* Set up cost improvement for usage of each profitable hard
2842 register for allocno A. */
2843 for (j = 0; j < class_size; j++)
2844 {
2845 hregno = ira_class_hard_regs[aclass][j];
2846 if (! check_hard_reg_p (a, hregno,
2847 conflicting_regs, profitable_hard_regs))
2848 continue;
2849 ira_assert (ira_class_hard_reg_index[aclass][hregno] == j);
2850 k = allocno_costs == NULL ? 0 : j;
2851 costs[hregno] = (allocno_costs == NULL
2852 ? ALLOCNO_UPDATED_CLASS_COST (a) : allocno_costs[k]);
2853 costs[hregno] -= allocno_copy_cost_saving (a, hregno);
2854 costs[hregno] -= base_cost;
2855 if (costs[hregno] < 0)
2856 try_p = true;
2857 }
2858 if (! try_p)
2859 /* There is no chance to improve the allocation cost by
2860 assigning hard register to allocno A even without spilling
2861 conflicting allocnos. */
2862 continue;
2863 mode = ALLOCNO_MODE (a);
2864 nwords = ALLOCNO_NUM_OBJECTS (a);
2865 /* Process each allocno conflicting with A and update the cost
2866 improvement for profitable hard registers of A. To use a
2867 hard register for A we need to spill some conflicting
2868 allocnos and that creates penalty for the cost
2869 improvement. */
2870 for (word = 0; word < nwords; word++)
2871 {
2872 ira_object_t conflict_obj;
2873 ira_object_t obj = ALLOCNO_OBJECT (a, word);
2874 ira_object_conflict_iterator oci;
2875
2876 FOR_EACH_OBJECT_CONFLICT (obj, conflict_obj, oci)
2877 {
2878 ira_allocno_t conflict_a = OBJECT_ALLOCNO (conflict_obj);
2879
2880 if (ALLOCNO_COLOR_DATA (conflict_a)->temp == check)
2881 /* We already processed this conflicting allocno
2882 because we processed earlier another object of the
2883 conflicting allocno. */
2884 continue;
2885 ALLOCNO_COLOR_DATA (conflict_a)->temp = check;
2886 if ((conflict_hregno = ALLOCNO_HARD_REGNO (conflict_a)) < 0)
2887 continue;
2888 spill_cost = ALLOCNO_UPDATED_MEMORY_COST (conflict_a);
2889 k = (ira_class_hard_reg_index
2890 [ALLOCNO_CLASS (conflict_a)][conflict_hregno]);
2891 ira_assert (k >= 0);
2892 if ((allocno_costs = ALLOCNO_HARD_REG_COSTS (conflict_a))
2893 != NULL)
2894 spill_cost -= allocno_costs[k];
2895 else
2896 spill_cost -= ALLOCNO_UPDATED_CLASS_COST (conflict_a);
2897 spill_cost
2898 += allocno_copy_cost_saving (conflict_a, conflict_hregno);
2899 conflict_nregs
2900 = hard_regno_nregs[conflict_hregno][ALLOCNO_MODE (conflict_a)];
2901 for (r = conflict_hregno;
2902 r >= 0 && r + hard_regno_nregs[r][mode] > conflict_hregno;
2903 r--)
2904 if (check_hard_reg_p (a, r,
2905 conflicting_regs, profitable_hard_regs))
2906 costs[r] += spill_cost;
2907 for (r = conflict_hregno + 1;
2908 r < conflict_hregno + conflict_nregs;
2909 r++)
2910 if (check_hard_reg_p (a, r,
2911 conflicting_regs, profitable_hard_regs))
2912 costs[r] += spill_cost;
2913 }
2914 }
2915 min_cost = INT_MAX;
2916 best = -1;
2917 /* Now we choose hard register for A which results in highest
2918 allocation cost improvement. */
2919 for (j = 0; j < class_size; j++)
2920 {
2921 hregno = ira_class_hard_regs[aclass][j];
2922 if (check_hard_reg_p (a, hregno,
2923 conflicting_regs, profitable_hard_regs)
2924 && min_cost > costs[hregno])
2925 {
2926 best = hregno;
2927 min_cost = costs[hregno];
2928 }
2929 }
2930 if (min_cost >= 0)
2931 /* We are in a situation when assigning any hard register to A
2932 by spilling some conflicting allocnos does not improve the
2933 allocation cost. */
2934 continue;
2935 nregs = hard_regno_nregs[best][mode];
2936 /* Now spill conflicting allocnos which contain a hard register
2937 of A when we assign the best chosen hard register to it. */
2938 for (word = 0; word < nwords; word++)
2939 {
2940 ira_object_t conflict_obj;
2941 ira_object_t obj = ALLOCNO_OBJECT (a, word);
2942 ira_object_conflict_iterator oci;
2943
2944 FOR_EACH_OBJECT_CONFLICT (obj, conflict_obj, oci)
2945 {
2946 ira_allocno_t conflict_a = OBJECT_ALLOCNO (conflict_obj);
2947
2948 if ((conflict_hregno = ALLOCNO_HARD_REGNO (conflict_a)) < 0)
2949 continue;
2950 conflict_nregs
2951 = hard_regno_nregs[conflict_hregno][ALLOCNO_MODE (conflict_a)];
2952 if (best + nregs <= conflict_hregno
2953 || conflict_hregno + conflict_nregs <= best)
2954 /* No intersection. */
2955 continue;
2956 ALLOCNO_HARD_REGNO (conflict_a) = -1;
2957 sorted_allocnos[n++] = conflict_a;
2958 if (internal_flag_ira_verbose > 2 && ira_dump_file != NULL)
2959 fprintf (ira_dump_file, "Spilling a%dr%d for a%dr%d\n",
2960 ALLOCNO_NUM (conflict_a), ALLOCNO_REGNO (conflict_a),
2961 ALLOCNO_NUM (a), ALLOCNO_REGNO (a));
2962 }
2963 }
2964 /* Assign the best chosen hard register to A. */
2965 ALLOCNO_HARD_REGNO (a) = best;
2966 if (internal_flag_ira_verbose > 2 && ira_dump_file != NULL)
2967 fprintf (ira_dump_file, "Assigning %d to a%dr%d\n",
2968 best, ALLOCNO_NUM (a), ALLOCNO_REGNO (a));
2969 }
2970 if (n == 0)
2971 return;
2972 /* We spilled some allocnos to assign their hard registers to other
2973 allocnos. The spilled allocnos are now in array
2974 'sorted_allocnos'. There is still a possibility that some of the
2975 spilled allocnos can get hard registers. So let us try assign
2976 them hard registers again (just a reminder -- function
2977 'assign_hard_reg' assigns hard registers only if it is possible
2978 and profitable). We process the spilled allocnos with biggest
2979 benefit to get hard register first -- see function
2980 'allocno_cost_compare_func'. */
2981 qsort (sorted_allocnos, n, sizeof (ira_allocno_t),
2982 allocno_cost_compare_func);
2983 for (j = 0; j < n; j++)
2984 {
2985 a = sorted_allocnos[j];
2986 ALLOCNO_ASSIGNED_P (a) = false;
2987 if (internal_flag_ira_verbose > 3 && ira_dump_file != NULL)
2988 {
2989 fprintf (ira_dump_file, " ");
2990 ira_print_expanded_allocno (a);
2991 fprintf (ira_dump_file, " -- ");
2992 }
2993 if (assign_hard_reg (a, false))
2994 {
2995 if (internal_flag_ira_verbose > 3 && ira_dump_file != NULL)
2996 fprintf (ira_dump_file, "assign hard reg %d\n",
2997 ALLOCNO_HARD_REGNO (a));
2998 }
2999 else
3000 {
3001 if (internal_flag_ira_verbose > 3 && ira_dump_file != NULL)
3002 fprintf (ira_dump_file, "assign memory\n");
3003 }
3004 }
3005}
3006
3007/* Sort allocnos according to their priorities. */
3008static int
3009allocno_priority_compare_func (const void *v1p, const void *v2p)
3010{
3011 ira_allocno_t a1 = *(const ira_allocno_t *) v1p;
3012 ira_allocno_t a2 = *(const ira_allocno_t *) v2p;
3013 int pri1, pri2;
3014
3015 /* Assign hard reg to static chain pointer pseudo first when
3016 non-local goto is used. */
3017 if (non_spilled_static_chain_regno_p (ALLOCNO_REGNO (a1)))
3018 return 1;
3019 else if (non_spilled_static_chain_regno_p (ALLOCNO_REGNO (a2)))
3020 return -1;
3021 pri1 = allocno_priorities[ALLOCNO_NUM (a1)];
3022 pri2 = allocno_priorities[ALLOCNO_NUM (a2)];
3023 if (pri2 != pri1)
3024 return SORTGT (pri2, pri1);
3025
3026 /* If regs are equally good, sort by allocnos, so that the results of
3027 qsort leave nothing to chance. */
3028 return ALLOCNO_NUM (a1) - ALLOCNO_NUM (a2);
3029}

3031/* Chaitin-Briggs coloring for allocnos in COLORING_ALLOCNO_BITMAP
3032 taking into account allocnos in CONSIDERATION_ALLOCNO_BITMAP. */
3033static void
3034color_allocnos (void)
3035{
3036 unsigned int i, n;
3037 bitmap_iterator bi;
3038 ira_allocno_t a;
3039
3040 setup_profitable_hard_regs ();
3041 EXECUTE_IF_SET_IN_BITMAP (coloring_allocno_bitmap, 0, i, bi)
3042 {
3043 int l, nr;
3044 HARD_REG_SET conflict_hard_regs;
3045 allocno_color_data_t data;
3046 ira_pref_t pref, next_pref;
3047
3048 a = ira_allocnos[i];
3049 nr = ALLOCNO_NUM_OBJECTS (a);
3050 CLEAR_HARD_REG_SET (conflict_hard_regs);
3051 for (l = 0; l < nr; l++)
3052 {
3053 ira_object_t obj = ALLOCNO_OBJECT (a, l);
3054 IOR_HARD_REG_SET (conflict_hard_regs,
3055 OBJECT_CONFLICT_HARD_REGS (obj));
3056 }
3057 data = ALLOCNO_COLOR_DATA (a);
3058 for (pref = ALLOCNO_PREFS (a); pref != NULL; pref = next_pref)
3059 {
3060 next_pref = pref->next_pref;
3061 if (! ira_hard_reg_in_set_p (pref->hard_regno,
3062 ALLOCNO_MODE (a),
3063 data->profitable_hard_regs))
3064 ira_remove_pref (pref);
3065 }
3066 }
3067 if (flag_ira_algorithm == IRA_ALGORITHM_PRIORITY)
3068 {
3069 n = 0;
3070 EXECUTE_IF_SET_IN_BITMAP (coloring_allocno_bitmap, 0, i, bi)
3071 {
3072 a = ira_allocnos[i];
3073 if (ALLOCNO_CLASS (a) == NO_REGS)
3074 {
3075 ALLOCNO_HARD_REGNO (a) = -1;
3076 ALLOCNO_ASSIGNED_P (a) = true;
3077 ira_assert (ALLOCNO_UPDATED_HARD_REG_COSTS (a) == NULL);
3078 ira_assert (ALLOCNO_UPDATED_CONFLICT_HARD_REG_COSTS (a) == NULL);
3079 if (internal_flag_ira_verbose > 3 && ira_dump_file != NULL)
3080 {
3081 fprintf (ira_dump_file, " Spill");
3082 ira_print_expanded_allocno (a);
3083 fprintf (ira_dump_file, "\n");
3084 }
3085 continue;
3086 }
3087 sorted_allocnos[n++] = a;
3088 }
3089 if (n != 0)
3090 {
3091 setup_allocno_priorities (sorted_allocnos, n);
3092 qsort (sorted_allocnos, n, sizeof (ira_allocno_t),
3093 allocno_priority_compare_func);
3094 for (i = 0; i < n; i++)
3095 {
3096 a = sorted_allocnos[i];
3097 if (internal_flag_ira_verbose > 3 && ira_dump_file != NULL)
3098 {
3099 fprintf (ira_dump_file, " ");
3100 ira_print_expanded_allocno (a);
3101 fprintf (ira_dump_file, " -- ");
3102 }
3103 if (assign_hard_reg (a, false))
3104 {
3105 if (internal_flag_ira_verbose > 3 && ira_dump_file != NULL)
3106 fprintf (ira_dump_file, "assign hard reg %d\n",
3107 ALLOCNO_HARD_REGNO (a));
3108 }
3109 else
3110 {
3111 if (internal_flag_ira_verbose > 3 && ira_dump_file != NULL)
3112 fprintf (ira_dump_file, "assign memory\n");
3113 }
3114 }
3115 }
3116 }
3117 else
3118 {
3119 form_allocno_hard_regs_nodes_forest ();
3120 if (internal_flag_ira_verbose > 2 && ira_dump_file != NULL)
3121 print_hard_regs_forest (ira_dump_file);
3122 EXECUTE_IF_SET_IN_BITMAP (coloring_allocno_bitmap, 0, i, bi)
3123 {
3124 a = ira_allocnos[i];
3125 if (ALLOCNO_CLASS (a) != NO_REGS && ! empty_profitable_hard_regs (a))
3126 {
3127 ALLOCNO_COLOR_DATA (a)->in_graph_p = true;
3128 update_costs_from_prefs (a);
3129 }
3130 else
3131 {
3132 ALLOCNO_HARD_REGNO (a) = -1;
3133 ALLOCNO_ASSIGNED_P (a) = true;
3134 /* We don't need updated costs anymore. */
3135 ira_free_allocno_updated_costs (a);
3136 if (internal_flag_ira_verbose > 3 && ira_dump_file != NULL)
3137 {
3138 fprintf (ira_dump_file, " Spill");
3139 ira_print_expanded_allocno (a);
3140 fprintf (ira_dump_file, "\n");
3141 }
3142 }
3143 }
3144 /* Put the allocnos into the corresponding buckets. */
3145 colorable_allocno_bucket = NULL;
3146 uncolorable_allocno_bucket = NULL;
3147 EXECUTE_IF_SET_IN_BITMAP (coloring_allocno_bitmap, 0, i, bi)
3148 {
3149 a = ira_allocnos[i];
3150 if (ALLOCNO_COLOR_DATA (a)->in_graph_p)
3151 put_allocno_into_bucket (a);
3152 }
3153 push_allocnos_to_stack ();
3154 pop_allocnos_from_stack ();
3155 finish_allocno_hard_regs_nodes_forest ();
3156 }
3157 improve_allocation ();
3158}

3221/* Color the allocnos inside loop (in the extreme case it can be all
3222 of the function) given the corresponding LOOP_TREE_NODE. The
3223 function is called for each loop during top-down traverse of the
3224 loop tree. */
3225static void
3226color_pass (ira_loop_tree_node_t loop_tree_node)
3227{
3228 int regno, hard_regno, index = -1, n;
3229 int cost, exit_freq, enter_freq;
3230 unsigned int j;
3231 bitmap_iterator bi;
3232 machine_mode mode;
3233 enum reg_class rclass, aclass, pclass;
3234 ira_allocno_t a, subloop_allocno;
3235 ira_loop_tree_node_t subloop_node;
3236
3237 ira_assert (loop_tree_node->bb == NULL);
3238 if (internal_flag_ira_verbose > 1 && ira_dump_file != NULL)
3239 print_loop_title (loop_tree_node);
3240
3241 bitmap_copy (coloring_allocno_bitmap, loop_tree_node->all_allocnos);
3242 bitmap_copy (consideration_allocno_bitmap, coloring_allocno_bitmap);
3243 n = 0;
3244 EXECUTE_IF_SET_IN_BITMAP (consideration_allocno_bitmap, 0, j, bi)
3245 {
3246 a = ira_allocnos[j];
3247 n++;
3248 if (! ALLOCNO_ASSIGNED_P (a))
3249 continue;
3250 bitmap_clear_bit (coloring_allocno_bitmap, ALLOCNO_NUM (a));
3251 }
3252 allocno_color_data
3253 = (allocno_color_data_t) ira_allocate (sizeof (struct allocno_color_data)
3254 * n);
3255 memset (allocno_color_data, 0, sizeof (struct allocno_color_data) * n);
3256 curr_allocno_process = 0;
3257 n = 0;
3258 EXECUTE_IF_SET_IN_BITMAP (consideration_allocno_bitmap, 0, j, bi)
3259 {
3260 a = ira_allocnos[j];
3261 ALLOCNO_ADD_DATA (a) = allocno_color_data + n;
3262 n++;
3263 }
3264 init_allocno_threads ();
3265 /* Color all mentioned allocnos including transparent ones. */
3266 color_allocnos ();
3267 /* Process caps. They are processed just once. */
3268 if (flag_ira_region == IRA_REGION_MIXED
3269 || flag_ira_region == IRA_REGION_ALL)
3270 EXECUTE_IF_SET_IN_BITMAP (loop_tree_node->all_allocnos, 0, j, bi)
3271 {
3272 a = ira_allocnos[j];
3273 if (ALLOCNO_CAP_MEMBER (a) == NULL)
3274 continue;
3275 /* Remove from processing in the next loop. */
3276 bitmap_clear_bit (consideration_allocno_bitmap, j);
3277 rclass = ALLOCNO_CLASS (a);
3278 pclass = ira_pressure_class_translate[rclass];
3279 if (flag_ira_region == IRA_REGION_MIXED
3280 && (loop_tree_node->reg_pressure[pclass]
3281 <= ira_class_hard_regs_num[pclass]))
3282 {
3283 mode = ALLOCNO_MODE (a);
3284 hard_regno = ALLOCNO_HARD_REGNO (a);
3285 if (hard_regno >= 0)
3286 {
3287 index = ira_class_hard_reg_index[rclass][hard_regno];
3288 ira_assert (index >= 0);
3289 }
3290 regno = ALLOCNO_REGNO (a);
3291 subloop_allocno = ALLOCNO_CAP_MEMBER (a);
3292 subloop_node = ALLOCNO_LOOP_TREE_NODE (subloop_allocno);
3293 ira_assert (!ALLOCNO_ASSIGNED_P (subloop_allocno));
3294 ALLOCNO_HARD_REGNO (subloop_allocno) = hard_regno;
3295 ALLOCNO_ASSIGNED_P (subloop_allocno) = true;
3296 if (hard_regno >= 0)
3297 update_costs_from_copies (subloop_allocno, true, true);
3298 /* We don't need updated costs anymore. */
3299 ira_free_allocno_updated_costs (subloop_allocno);
3300 }
3301 }
3302 /* Update costs of the corresponding allocnos (not caps) in the
3303 subloops. */
3304 for (subloop_node = loop_tree_node->subloops;
3305 subloop_node != NULL;
3306 subloop_node = subloop_node->subloop_next)
3307 {
3308 ira_assert (subloop_node->bb == NULL);
3309 EXECUTE_IF_SET_IN_BITMAP (consideration_allocno_bitmap, 0, j, bi)
3310 {
3311 a = ira_allocnos[j];
3312 ira_assert (ALLOCNO_CAP_MEMBER (a) == NULL);
3313 mode = ALLOCNO_MODE (a);
3314 rclass = ALLOCNO_CLASS (a);
3315 pclass = ira_pressure_class_translate[rclass];
3316 hard_regno = ALLOCNO_HARD_REGNO (a);
3317 /* Use hard register class here. ??? */
3318 if (hard_regno >= 0)
3319 {
3320 index = ira_class_hard_reg_index[rclass][hard_regno];
3321 ira_assert (index >= 0);
3322 }
3323 regno = ALLOCNO_REGNO (a);
3324 /* ??? conflict costs */
3325 subloop_allocno = subloop_node->regno_allocno_map[regno];
3326 if (subloop_allocno == NULL
3327 || ALLOCNO_CAP (subloop_allocno) != NULL)
3328 continue;
3329 ira_assert (ALLOCNO_CLASS (subloop_allocno) == rclass);
3330 ira_assert (bitmap_bit_p (subloop_node->all_allocnos,
3331 ALLOCNO_NUM (subloop_allocno)));
3332 if ((flag_ira_region == IRA_REGION_MIXED
3333 && (loop_tree_node->reg_pressure[pclass]
3334 <= ira_class_hard_regs_num[pclass]))
3335 || (pic_offset_table_rtx != NULL
3336 && regno == (int) REGNO (pic_offset_table_rtx))
3337 /* Avoid overlapped multi-registers. Moves between them
3338 might result in wrong code generation. */
3339 || (hard_regno >= 0
3340 && ira_reg_class_max_nregs[pclass][mode] > 1))
3341 {
3342 if (! ALLOCNO_ASSIGNED_P (subloop_allocno))
3343 {
3344 ALLOCNO_HARD_REGNO (subloop_allocno) = hard_regno;
3345 ALLOCNO_ASSIGNED_P (subloop_allocno) = true;
3346 if (hard_regno >= 0)
3347 update_costs_from_copies (subloop_allocno, true, true);
3348 /* We don't need updated costs anymore. */
3349 ira_free_allocno_updated_costs (subloop_allocno);
3350 }
3351 continue;
3352 }
3353 exit_freq = ira_loop_edge_freq (subloop_node, regno, true);
3354 enter_freq = ira_loop_edge_freq (subloop_node, regno, false);
3355 ira_assert (regno < ira_reg_equiv_len);
3356 if (ira_equiv_no_lvalue_p (regno))
3357 {
3358 if (! ALLOCNO_ASSIGNED_P (subloop_allocno))
3359 {
3360 ALLOCNO_HARD_REGNO (subloop_allocno) = hard_regno;
3361 ALLOCNO_ASSIGNED_P (subloop_allocno) = true;
3362 if (hard_regno >= 0)
3363 update_costs_from_copies (subloop_allocno, true, true);
3364 /* We don't need updated costs anymore. */
3365 ira_free_allocno_updated_costs (subloop_allocno);
3366 }
3367 }
3368 else if (hard_regno < 0)
3369 {
3370 ALLOCNO_UPDATED_MEMORY_COST (subloop_allocno)
3371 -= ((ira_memory_move_cost[mode][rclass][1] * enter_freq)
3372 + (ira_memory_move_cost[mode][rclass][0] * exit_freq));
3373 }
3374 else
3375 {
3376 aclass = ALLOCNO_CLASS (subloop_allocno);
3377 ira_init_register_move_cost_if_necessary (mode);
3378 cost = (ira_register_move_cost[mode][rclass][rclass]
3379 * (exit_freq + enter_freq));
3380 ira_allocate_and_set_or_copy_costs
3381 (&ALLOCNO_UPDATED_HARD_REG_COSTS (subloop_allocno), aclass,
3382 ALLOCNO_UPDATED_CLASS_COST (subloop_allocno),
3383 ALLOCNO_HARD_REG_COSTS (subloop_allocno));
3384 ira_allocate_and_set_or_copy_costs
3385 (&ALLOCNO_UPDATED_CONFLICT_HARD_REG_COSTS (subloop_allocno),
3386 aclass, 0, ALLOCNO_CONFLICT_HARD_REG_COSTS (subloop_allocno));
3387 ALLOCNO_UPDATED_HARD_REG_COSTS (subloop_allocno)[index] -= cost;
3388 ALLOCNO_UPDATED_CONFLICT_HARD_REG_COSTS (subloop_allocno)[index]
3389 -= cost;
3390 if (ALLOCNO_UPDATED_CLASS_COST (subloop_allocno)
3391 > ALLOCNO_UPDATED_HARD_REG_COSTS (subloop_allocno)[index])
3392 ALLOCNO_UPDATED_CLASS_COST (subloop_allocno)
3393 = ALLOCNO_UPDATED_HARD_REG_COSTS (subloop_allocno)[index];
3394 ALLOCNO_UPDATED_MEMORY_COST (subloop_allocno)
3395 += (ira_memory_move_cost[mode][rclass][0] * enter_freq
3396 + ira_memory_move_cost[mode][rclass][1] * exit_freq);
3397 }
3398 }
3399 }
3400 ira_free (allocno_color_data);
3401 EXECUTE_IF_SET_IN_BITMAP (consideration_allocno_bitmap, 0, j, bi)
3402 {
3403 a = ira_allocnos[j];
3404 ALLOCNO_ADD_DATA (a) = NULL;
3405 }
3406}

3408/* Initialize the common data for coloring and calls functions to do
3409 Chaitin-Briggs and regional coloring. */
3410static void
3411do_coloring (void)
3412{
3413 coloring_allocno_bitmap = ira_allocate_bitmap ();
3414 if (internal_flag_ira_verbose > 0 && ira_dump_file != NULL)
3415 fprintf (ira_dump_file, "\n**** Allocnos coloring:\n\n");
3416
3417 ira_traverse_loop_tree (false, ira_loop_tree_root, color_pass, NULL);
3418
3419 if (internal_flag_ira_verbose > 1 && ira_dump_file != NULL)
3420 ira_print_disposition (ira_dump_file);
3421
3422 ira_free_bitmap (coloring_allocno_bitmap);
3423}

3427/* Move spill/restore code, which are to be generated in ira-emit.c,
3428 to less frequent points (if it is profitable) by reassigning some
3429 allocnos (in loop with subloops containing in another loop) to
3430 memory which results in longer live-range where the corresponding
3431 pseudo-registers will be in memory. */
3432static void
3433move_spill_restore (void)
3434{
3435 int cost, regno, hard_regno, hard_regno2, index;
3436 bool changed_p;
3437 int enter_freq, exit_freq;
3438 machine_mode mode;
3439 enum reg_class rclass;
3440 ira_allocno_t a, parent_allocno, subloop_allocno;
3441 ira_loop_tree_node_t parent, loop_node, subloop_node;
3442 ira_allocno_iterator ai;
3443
3444 for (;;)
3445 {
3446 changed_p = false;
3447 if (internal_flag_ira_verbose > 0 && ira_dump_file != NULL)
3448 fprintf (ira_dump_file, "New iteration of spill/restore move\n");
3449 FOR_EACH_ALLOCNO (a, ai)
3450 {
3451 regno = ALLOCNO_REGNO (a);
3452 loop_node = ALLOCNO_LOOP_TREE_NODE (a);
3453 if (ALLOCNO_CAP_MEMBER (a) != NULL
3454 || ALLOCNO_CAP (a) != NULL
3455 || (hard_regno = ALLOCNO_HARD_REGNO (a)) < 0
3456 || loop_node->children == NULL
3457 /* don't do the optimization because it can create
3458 copies and the reload pass can spill the allocno set
3459 by copy although the allocno will not get memory
3460 slot. */
3461 || ira_equiv_no_lvalue_p (regno)
3462 || !bitmap_bit_p (loop_node->border_allocnos, ALLOCNO_NUM (a))
3463 /* Do not spill static chain pointer pseudo when
3464 non-local goto is used. */
3465 || non_spilled_static_chain_regno_p (regno))
3466 continue;
3467 mode = ALLOCNO_MODE (a);
3468 rclass = ALLOCNO_CLASS (a);
3469 index = ira_class_hard_reg_index[rclass][hard_regno];
3470 ira_assert (index >= 0);
3471 cost = (ALLOCNO_MEMORY_COST (a)
3472 - (ALLOCNO_HARD_REG_COSTS (a) == NULL
3473 ? ALLOCNO_CLASS_COST (a)
3474 : ALLOCNO_HARD_REG_COSTS (a)[index]));
3475 ira_init_register_move_cost_if_necessary (mode);
3476 for (subloop_node = loop_node->subloops;
3477 subloop_node != NULL;
3478 subloop_node = subloop_node->subloop_next)
3479 {
3480 ira_assert (subloop_node->bb == NULL);
3481 subloop_allocno = subloop_node->regno_allocno_map[regno];
3482 if (subloop_allocno == NULL)
3483 continue;
3484 ira_assert (rclass == ALLOCNO_CLASS (subloop_allocno));
3485 /* We have accumulated cost. To get the real cost of
3486 allocno usage in the loop we should subtract costs of
3487 the subloop allocnos. */
3488 cost -= (ALLOCNO_MEMORY_COST (subloop_allocno)
3489 - (ALLOCNO_HARD_REG_COSTS (subloop_allocno) == NULL
3490 ? ALLOCNO_CLASS_COST (subloop_allocno)
3491 : ALLOCNO_HARD_REG_COSTS (subloop_allocno)[index]));
3492 exit_freq = ira_loop_edge_freq (subloop_node, regno, true);
3493 enter_freq = ira_loop_edge_freq (subloop_node, regno, false);
3494 if ((hard_regno2 = ALLOCNO_HARD_REGNO (subloop_allocno)) < 0)
3495 cost -= (ira_memory_move_cost[mode][rclass][0] * exit_freq
3496 + ira_memory_move_cost[mode][rclass][1] * enter_freq);
3497 else
3498 {
3499 cost
3500 += (ira_memory_move_cost[mode][rclass][0] * exit_freq
3501 + ira_memory_move_cost[mode][rclass][1] * enter_freq);
3502 if (hard_regno2 != hard_regno)
3503 cost -= (ira_register_move_cost[mode][rclass][rclass]
3504 * (exit_freq + enter_freq));
3505 }
3506 }
3507 if ((parent = loop_node->parent) != NULL
3508 && (parent_allocno = parent->regno_allocno_map[regno]) != NULL)
3509 {
3510 ira_assert (rclass == ALLOCNO_CLASS (parent_allocno));
3511 exit_freq = ira_loop_edge_freq (loop_node, regno, true);
3512 enter_freq = ira_loop_edge_freq (loop_node, regno, false);
3513 if ((hard_regno2 = ALLOCNO_HARD_REGNO (parent_allocno)) < 0)
3514 cost -= (ira_memory_move_cost[mode][rclass][0] * exit_freq
3515 + ira_memory_move_cost[mode][rclass][1] * enter_freq);
3516 else
3517 {
3518 cost
3519 += (ira_memory_move_cost[mode][rclass][1] * exit_freq
3520 + ira_memory_move_cost[mode][rclass][0] * enter_freq);
3521 if (hard_regno2 != hard_regno)
3522 cost -= (ira_register_move_cost[mode][rclass][rclass]
3523 * (exit_freq + enter_freq));
3524 }
3525 }
3526 if (cost < 0)
3527 {
3528 ALLOCNO_HARD_REGNO (a) = -1;
3529 if (internal_flag_ira_verbose > 3 && ira_dump_file != NULL)
3530 {
3531 fprintf
3532 (ira_dump_file,
3533 " Moving spill/restore for a%dr%d up from loop %d",
3534 ALLOCNO_NUM (a), regno, loop_node->loop_num);
3535 fprintf (ira_dump_file, " - profit %d\n", -cost);
3536 }
3537 changed_p = true;
3538 }
3539 }
3540 if (! changed_p)
3541 break;
3542 }
3543}

3546
3547/* Update current hard reg costs and current conflict hard reg costs
3548 for allocno A. It is done by processing its copies containing
3549 other allocnos already assigned. */
3550static void
3551update_curr_costs (ira_allocno_t a)
3552{
3553 int i, hard_regno, cost;
3554 machine_mode mode;
3555 enum reg_class aclass, rclass;
3556 ira_allocno_t another_a;
3557 ira_copy_t cp, next_cp;
3558
3559 ira_free_allocno_updated_costs (a);
3560 ira_assert (! ALLOCNO_ASSIGNED_P (a));
3561 aclass = ALLOCNO_CLASS (a);
3562 if (aclass == NO_REGS)
3563 return;
3564 mode = ALLOCNO_MODE (a);
3565 ira_init_register_move_cost_if_necessary (mode);
3566 for (cp = ALLOCNO_COPIES (a); cp != NULL; cp = next_cp)
3567 {
3568 if (cp->first == a)
3569 {
3570 next_cp = cp->next_first_allocno_copy;
3571 another_a = cp->second;
3572 }
3573 else if (cp->second == a)
3574 {
3575 next_cp = cp->next_second_allocno_copy;
3576 another_a = cp->first;
3577 }
3578 else
3579 gcc_unreachable ();
3580 if (! ira_reg_classes_intersect_p[aclass][ALLOCNO_CLASS (another_a)]
3581 || ! ALLOCNO_ASSIGNED_P (another_a)
3582 || (hard_regno = ALLOCNO_HARD_REGNO (another_a)) < 0)
3583 continue;
3584 rclass = REGNO_REG_CLASS (hard_regno);
3585 i = ira_class_hard_reg_index[aclass][hard_regno];
3586 if (i < 0)
3587 continue;
3588 cost = (cp->first == a
3589 ? ira_register_move_cost[mode][rclass][aclass]
3590 : ira_register_move_cost[mode][aclass][rclass]);
3591 ira_allocate_and_set_or_copy_costs
3592 (&ALLOCNO_UPDATED_HARD_REG_COSTS (a), aclass, ALLOCNO_CLASS_COST (a),
3593 ALLOCNO_HARD_REG_COSTS (a));
3594 ira_allocate_and_set_or_copy_costs
3595 (&ALLOCNO_UPDATED_CONFLICT_HARD_REG_COSTS (a),
3596 aclass, 0, ALLOCNO_CONFLICT_HARD_REG_COSTS (a));
3597 ALLOCNO_UPDATED_HARD_REG_COSTS (a)[i] -= cp->freq * cost;
3598 ALLOCNO_UPDATED_CONFLICT_HARD_REG_COSTS (a)[i] -= cp->freq * cost;
3599 }
3600}

3602/* Try to assign hard registers to the unassigned allocnos and
3603 allocnos conflicting with them or conflicting with allocnos whose
3604 regno >= START_REGNO. The function is called after ira_flattening,
3605 so more allocnos (including ones created in ira-emit.c) will have a
3606 chance to get a hard register. We use simple assignment algorithm
3607 based on priorities. */
3608void
3609ira_reassign_conflict_allocnos (int start_regno)
3610{
3611 int i, allocnos_to_color_num;
3612 ira_allocno_t a;
3613 enum reg_class aclass;
3614 bitmap allocnos_to_color;
3615 ira_allocno_iterator ai;
3616
3617 allocnos_to_color = ira_allocate_bitmap ();
3618 allocnos_to_color_num = 0;
3619 FOR_EACH_ALLOCNO (a, ai)
3620 {
3621 int n = ALLOCNO_NUM_OBJECTS (a);
3622
3623 if (! ALLOCNO_ASSIGNED_P (a)
3624 && ! bitmap_bit_p (allocnos_to_color, ALLOCNO_NUM (a)))
3625 {
3626 if (ALLOCNO_CLASS (a) != NO_REGS)
3627 sorted_allocnos[allocnos_to_color_num++] = a;
3628 else
3629 {
3630 ALLOCNO_ASSIGNED_P (a) = true;
3631 ALLOCNO_HARD_REGNO (a) = -1;
3632 ira_assert (ALLOCNO_UPDATED_HARD_REG_COSTS (a) == NULL);
3633 ira_assert (ALLOCNO_UPDATED_CONFLICT_HARD_REG_COSTS (a) == NULL);
3634 }
3635 bitmap_set_bit (allocnos_to_color, ALLOCNO_NUM (a));
3636 }
3637 if (ALLOCNO_REGNO (a) < start_regno
3638 || (aclass = ALLOCNO_CLASS (a)) == NO_REGS)
3639 continue;
3640 for (i = 0; i < n; i++)
3641 {
3642 ira_object_t obj = ALLOCNO_OBJECT (a, i);
3643 ira_object_t conflict_obj;
3644 ira_object_conflict_iterator oci;
3645
3646 FOR_EACH_OBJECT_CONFLICT (obj, conflict_obj, oci)
3647 {
3648 ira_allocno_t conflict_a = OBJECT_ALLOCNO (conflict_obj);
3649
3650 ira_assert (ira_reg_classes_intersect_p
3651 [aclass][ALLOCNO_CLASS (conflict_a)]);
3652 if (!bitmap_set_bit (allocnos_to_color, ALLOCNO_NUM (conflict_a)))
3653 continue;
3654 sorted_allocnos[allocnos_to_color_num++] = conflict_a;
3655 }
3656 }
3657 }
3658 ira_free_bitmap (allocnos_to_color);
3659 if (allocnos_to_color_num > 1)
3660 {
3661 setup_allocno_priorities (sorted_allocnos, allocnos_to_color_num);
3662 qsort (sorted_allocnos, allocnos_to_color_num, sizeof (ira_allocno_t),
3663 allocno_priority_compare_func);
3664 }
3665 for (i = 0; i < allocnos_to_color_num; i++)
3666 {
3667 a = sorted_allocnos[i];
3668 ALLOCNO_ASSIGNED_P (a) = false;
3669 update_curr_costs (a);
3670 }
3671 for (i = 0; i < allocnos_to_color_num; i++)
3672 {
3673 a = sorted_allocnos[i];
3674 if (assign_hard_reg (a, true))
3675 {
3676 if (internal_flag_ira_verbose > 3 && ira_dump_file != NULL)
3677 fprintf
3678 (ira_dump_file,
3679 " Secondary allocation: assign hard reg %d to reg %d\n",
3680 ALLOCNO_HARD_REGNO (a), ALLOCNO_REGNO (a));
3681 }
3682 }
3683}

3714/* This page contains code to coalesce memory stack slots used by
3715 spilled allocnos. This results in smaller stack frame, better data
3716 locality, and in smaller code for some architectures like
3717 x86/x86_64 where insn size depends on address displacement value.
3718 On the other hand, it can worsen insn scheduling after the RA but
3719 in practice it is less important than smaller stack frames. */
3720
3721/* TRUE if we coalesced some allocnos. In other words, if we got
3722 loops formed by members first_coalesced_allocno and
3723 next_coalesced_allocno containing more one allocno. */
3724static bool allocno_coalesced_p;
3725
3726/* Bitmap used to prevent a repeated allocno processing because of
3727 coalescing. */
3728static bitmap processed_coalesced_allocno_bitmap;
3729
3730/* See below. */
3731typedef struct coalesce_data *coalesce_data_t;
3732
3733/* To decrease footprint of ira_allocno structure we store all data
3734 needed only for coalescing in the following structure. */
3735struct coalesce_data
3736{
3737 /* Coalesced allocnos form a cyclic list. One allocno given by
3738 FIRST represents all coalesced allocnos. The
3739 list is chained by NEXT. */
3740 ira_allocno_t first;
3741 ira_allocno_t next;
3742 int temp;
3743};
3744
3745/* Container for storing allocno data concerning coalescing. */
3746static coalesce_data_t allocno_coalesce_data;
3747
3748/* Macro to access the data concerning coalescing. */
3749#define ALLOCNO_COALESCE_DATA(a) ((coalesce_data_t) ALLOCNO_ADD_DATA (a))
3750
3751/* Merge two sets of coalesced allocnos given correspondingly by
3752 allocnos A1 and A2 (more accurately merging A2 set into A1
3753 set). */
3754static void
3755merge_allocnos (ira_allocno_t a1, ira_allocno_t a2)
3756{
3757 ira_allocno_t a, first, last, next;
3758
3759 first = ALLOCNO_COALESCE_DATA (a1)->first;
3760 a = ALLOCNO_COALESCE_DATA (a2)->first;
3761 if (first == a)
3762 return;
3763 for (last = a2, a = ALLOCNO_COALESCE_DATA (a2)->next;;
3764 a = ALLOCNO_COALESCE_DATA (a)->next)
3765 {
3766 ALLOCNO_COALESCE_DATA (a)->first = first;
3767 if (a == a2)
3768 break;
3769 last = a;
3770 }
3771 next = allocno_coalesce_data[ALLOCNO_NUM (first)].next;
3772 allocno_coalesce_data[ALLOCNO_NUM (first)].next = a2;
3773 allocno_coalesce_data[ALLOCNO_NUM (last)].next = next;
3774}
3775
3776/* Return TRUE if there are conflicting allocnos from two sets of
3777 coalesced allocnos given correspondingly by allocnos A1 and A2. We
3778 use live ranges to find conflicts because conflicts are represented
3779 only for allocnos of the same allocno class and during the reload
3780 pass we coalesce allocnos for sharing stack memory slots. */
3781static bool
3782coalesced_allocno_conflict_p (ira_allocno_t a1, ira_allocno_t a2)
3783{
3784 ira_allocno_t a, conflict_a;
3785
3786 if (allocno_coalesced_p)
3787 {
3788 bitmap_clear (processed_coalesced_allocno_bitmap);
3789 for (a = ALLOCNO_COALESCE_DATA (a1)->next;;
3790 a = ALLOCNO_COALESCE_DATA (a)->next)
3791 {
3792 bitmap_set_bit (processed_coalesced_allocno_bitmap, ALLOCNO_NUM (a));
3793 if (a == a1)
3794 break;
3795 }
3796 }
3797 for (a = ALLOCNO_COALESCE_DATA (a2)->next;;
3798 a = ALLOCNO_COALESCE_DATA (a)->next)
3799 {
3800 for (conflict_a = ALLOCNO_COALESCE_DATA (a1)->next;;
3801 conflict_a = ALLOCNO_COALESCE_DATA (conflict_a)->next)
3802 {
3803 if (allocnos_conflict_by_live_ranges_p (a, conflict_a))
3804 return true;
3805 if (conflict_a == a1)
3806 break;
3807 }
3808 if (a == a2)
3809 break;
3810 }
3811 return false;
3812}
3813
3814/* The major function for aggressive allocno coalescing. We coalesce
3815 only spilled allocnos. If some allocnos have been coalesced, we
3816 set up flag allocno_coalesced_p. */
3817static void
3818coalesce_allocnos (void)
3819{
3820 ira_allocno_t a;
3821 ira_copy_t cp, next_cp;
3822 unsigned int j;
3823 int i, n, cp_num, regno;
3824 bitmap_iterator bi;
3825
3826 cp_num = 0;
3827 /* Collect copies. */
3828 EXECUTE_IF_SET_IN_BITMAP (coloring_allocno_bitmap, 0, j, bi)
3829 {
3830 a = ira_allocnos[j];
3831 regno = ALLOCNO_REGNO (a);
3832 if (! ALLOCNO_ASSIGNED_P (a) || ALLOCNO_HARD_REGNO (a) >= 0
3833 || ira_equiv_no_lvalue_p (regno))
3834 continue;
3835 for (cp = ALLOCNO_COPIES (a); cp != NULL; cp = next_cp)
3836 {
3837 if (cp->first == a)
3838 {
3839 next_cp = cp->next_first_allocno_copy;
3840 regno = ALLOCNO_REGNO (cp->second);
3841 /* For priority coloring we coalesce allocnos only with
3842 the same allocno class not with intersected allocno
3843 classes as it were possible. It is done for
3844 simplicity. */
3845 if ((cp->insn != NULL || cp->constraint_p)
3846 && ALLOCNO_ASSIGNED_P (cp->second)
3847 && ALLOCNO_HARD_REGNO (cp->second) < 0
3848 && ! ira_equiv_no_lvalue_p (regno))
3849 sorted_copies[cp_num++] = cp;
3850 }
3851 else if (cp->second == a)
3852 next_cp = cp->next_second_allocno_copy;
3853 else
3854 gcc_unreachable ();
3855 }
3856 }
3857 qsort (sorted_copies, cp_num, sizeof (ira_copy_t), copy_freq_compare_func);
3858 /* Coalesced copies, most frequently executed first. */
3859 for (; cp_num != 0;)
3860 {
3861 for (i = 0; i < cp_num; i++)
3862 {
3863 cp = sorted_copies[i];
3864 if (! coalesced_allocno_conflict_p (cp->first, cp->second))
3865 {
3866 allocno_coalesced_p = true;
3867 if (internal_flag_ira_verbose > 3 && ira_dump_file != NULL)
3868 fprintf
3869 (ira_dump_file,
3870 " Coalescing copy %d:a%dr%d-a%dr%d (freq=%d)\n",
3871 cp->num, ALLOCNO_NUM (cp->first), ALLOCNO_REGNO (cp->first),
3872 ALLOCNO_NUM (cp->second), ALLOCNO_REGNO (cp->second),
3873 cp->freq);
3874 merge_allocnos (cp->first, cp->second);
3875 i++;
3876 break;
3877 }
3878 }
3879 /* Collect the rest of copies. */
3880 for (n = 0; i < cp_num; i++)
3881 {
3882 cp = sorted_copies[i];
3883 if (allocno_coalesce_data[ALLOCNO_NUM (cp->first)].first
3884 != allocno_coalesce_data[ALLOCNO_NUM (cp->second)].first)
3885 sorted_copies[n++] = cp;
3886 }
3887 cp_num = n;
3888 }
3889}

3891/* Usage cost and order number of coalesced allocno set to which
3892 given pseudo register belongs to. */
3893static int *regno_coalesced_allocno_cost;
3894static int *regno_coalesced_allocno_num;
3895
3896/* Sort pseudos according frequencies of coalesced allocno sets they
3897 belong to (putting most frequently ones first), and according to
3898 coalesced allocno set order numbers. */
3899static int
3900coalesced_pseudo_reg_freq_compare (const void *v1p, const void *v2p)
3901{
3902 const int regno1 = *(const int *) v1p;
3903 const int regno2 = *(const int *) v2p;
3904 int diff;
3905
3906 if ((diff = (regno_coalesced_allocno_cost[regno2]
3907 - regno_coalesced_allocno_cost[regno1])) != 0)
3908 return diff;
3909 if ((diff = (regno_coalesced_allocno_num[regno1]
3910 - regno_coalesced_allocno_num[regno2])) != 0)
3911 return diff;
3912 return regno1 - regno2;
3913}
3914
3915/* Widest width in which each pseudo reg is referred to (via subreg).
3916 It is used for sorting pseudo registers. */
3917static unsigned int *regno_max_ref_width;
3918
3919/* Sort pseudos according their slot numbers (putting ones with
3920 smaller numbers first, or last when the frame pointer is not
3921 needed). */
3922static int
3923coalesced_pseudo_reg_slot_compare (const void *v1p, const void *v2p)
3924{
3925 const int regno1 = *(const int *) v1p;
3926 const int regno2 = *(const int *) v2p;
3927 ira_allocno_t a1 = ira_regno_allocno_map[regno1];
3928 ira_allocno_t a2 = ira_regno_allocno_map[regno2];
3929 int diff, slot_num1, slot_num2;
3930 int total_size1, total_size2;
3931
3932 if (a1 == NULL || ALLOCNO_HARD_REGNO (a1) >= 0)
3933 {
3934 if (a2 == NULL || ALLOCNO_HARD_REGNO (a2) >= 0)
3935 return regno1 - regno2;
3936 return 1;
3937 }
3938 else if (a2 == NULL || ALLOCNO_HARD_REGNO (a2) >= 0)
3939 return -1;
3940 slot_num1 = -ALLOCNO_HARD_REGNO (a1);
3941 slot_num2 = -ALLOCNO_HARD_REGNO (a2);
3942 if ((diff = slot_num1 - slot_num2) != 0)
3943 return (frame_pointer_needed
3944 || (!FRAME_GROWS_DOWNWARD) == STACK_GROWS_DOWNWARD ? diff : -diff);
3945 total_size1 = MAX (PSEUDO_REGNO_BYTES (regno1),
3946 regno_max_ref_width[regno1]);
3947 total_size2 = MAX (PSEUDO_REGNO_BYTES (regno2),
3948 regno_max_ref_width[regno2]);
3949 if ((diff = total_size2 - total_size1) != 0)
3950 return diff;
3951 return regno1 - regno2;
3952}

3954/* Setup REGNO_COALESCED_ALLOCNO_COST and REGNO_COALESCED_ALLOCNO_NUM
3955 for coalesced allocno sets containing allocnos with their regnos
3956 given in array PSEUDO_REGNOS of length N. */
3957static void
3958setup_coalesced_allocno_costs_and_nums (int *pseudo_regnos, int n)
3959{
3960 int i, num, regno, cost;
3961 ira_allocno_t allocno, a;
3962
3963 for (num = i = 0; i < n; i++)
3964 {
3965 regno = pseudo_regnos[i];
3966 allocno = ira_regno_allocno_map[regno];
3967 if (allocno == NULL)
3968 {
3969 regno_coalesced_allocno_cost[regno] = 0;
3970 regno_coalesced_allocno_num[regno] = ++num;
3971 continue;
3972 }
3973 if (ALLOCNO_COALESCE_DATA (allocno)->first != allocno)
3974 continue;
3975 num++;
3976 for (cost = 0, a = ALLOCNO_COALESCE_DATA (allocno)->next;;
3977 a = ALLOCNO_COALESCE_DATA (a)->next)
3978 {
3979 cost += ALLOCNO_FREQ (a);
3980 if (a == allocno)
3981 break;
3982 }
3983 for (a = ALLOCNO_COALESCE_DATA (allocno)->next;;
3984 a = ALLOCNO_COALESCE_DATA (a)->next)
3985 {
3986 regno_coalesced_allocno_num[ALLOCNO_REGNO (a)] = num;
3987 regno_coalesced_allocno_cost[ALLOCNO_REGNO (a)] = cost;
3988 if (a == allocno)
3989 break;
3990 }
3991 }
3992}

3994/* Collect spilled allocnos representing coalesced allocno sets (the
3995 first coalesced allocno). The collected allocnos are returned
3996 through array SPILLED_COALESCED_ALLOCNOS. The function returns the
3997 number of the collected allocnos. The allocnos are given by their
3998 regnos in array PSEUDO_REGNOS of length N. */
3999static int
4000collect_spilled_coalesced_allocnos (int *pseudo_regnos, int n,
4001 ira_allocno_t *spilled_coalesced_allocnos)
4002{
4003 int i, num, regno;
4004 ira_allocno_t allocno;
4005
4006 for (num = i = 0; i < n; i++)
4007 {
4008 regno = pseudo_regnos[i];
4009 allocno = ira_regno_allocno_map[regno];
4010 if (allocno == NULL || ALLOCNO_HARD_REGNO (allocno) >= 0
4011 || ALLOCNO_COALESCE_DATA (allocno)->first != allocno)
4012 continue;

4018/* Array of live ranges of size IRA_ALLOCNOS_NUM. Live range for
4019 given slot contains live ranges of coalesced allocnos assigned to
4020 given slot. */
4021static live_range_t *slot_coalesced_allocnos_live_ranges;
4022
4023/* Return TRUE if coalesced allocnos represented by ALLOCNO has live
4024 ranges intersected with live ranges of coalesced allocnos assigned
4025 to slot with number N. */
4026static bool
4027slot_coalesced_allocno_live_ranges_intersect_p (ira_allocno_t allocno, int n)
4028{
4029 ira_allocno_t a;
4030
4031 for (a = ALLOCNO_COALESCE_DATA (allocno)->next;;
4032 a = ALLOCNO_COALESCE_DATA (a)->next)
4033 {
4034 int i;
4035 int nr = ALLOCNO_NUM_OBJECTS (a);
4036
4037 for (i = 0; i < nr; i++)
4038 {
4039 ira_object_t obj = ALLOCNO_OBJECT (a, i);
4040
4041 if (ira_live_ranges_intersect_p
4042 (slot_coalesced_allocnos_live_ranges[n],
4043 OBJECT_LIVE_RANGES (obj)))
4044 return true;
4045 }
4046 if (a == allocno)
4047 break;
4048 }
4049 return false;
4050}

4052/* Update live ranges of slot to which coalesced allocnos represented
4053 by ALLOCNO were assigned. */
4054static void
4055setup_slot_coalesced_allocno_live_ranges (ira_allocno_t allocno)
4056{
4057 int i, n;
4058 ira_allocno_t a;
4059 live_range_t r;
4060
4061 n = ALLOCNO_COALESCE_DATA (allocno)->temp;
4062 for (a = ALLOCNO_COALESCE_DATA (allocno)->next;;
4063 a = ALLOCNO_COALESCE_DATA (a)->next)
4064 {
4065 int nr = ALLOCNO_NUM_OBJECTS (a);
4066 for (i = 0; i < nr; i++)
4067 {
4068 ira_object_t obj = ALLOCNO_OBJECT (a, i);
4069
4070 r = ira_copy_live_range_list (OBJECT_LIVE_RANGES (obj));
4071 slot_coalesced_allocnos_live_ranges[n]
4072 = ira_merge_live_ranges
4073 (slot_coalesced_allocnos_live_ranges[n], r);
4074 }
4075 if (a == allocno)
4076 break;
4077 }
4078}
4079
4080/* We have coalesced allocnos involving in copies. Coalesce allocnos
4081 further in order to share the same memory stack slot. Allocnos
4082 representing sets of allocnos coalesced before the call are given
4083 in array SPILLED_COALESCED_ALLOCNOS of length NUM. Return TRUE if
4084 some allocnos were coalesced in the function. */
4085static bool
4086coalesce_spill_slots (ira_allocno_t *spilled_coalesced_allocnos, int num)
4087{
4088 int i, j, n, last_coalesced_allocno_num;
4089 ira_allocno_t allocno, a;
4090 bool merged_p = false;
4091 bitmap set_jump_crosses = regstat_get_setjmp_crosses ();
4092
4093 slot_coalesced_allocnos_live_ranges
4094 = (live_range_t *) ira_allocate (sizeof (live_range_t) * ira_allocnos_num);
4095 memset (slot_coalesced_allocnos_live_ranges, 0,
4096 sizeof (live_range_t) * ira_allocnos_num);
4097 last_coalesced_allocno_num = 0;
4098 /* Coalesce non-conflicting spilled allocnos preferring most
4099 frequently used. */
4100 for (i = 0; i < num; i++)
4101 {
4102 allocno = spilled_coalesced_allocnos[i];
4103 if (ALLOCNO_COALESCE_DATA (allocno)->first != allocno
4104 || bitmap_bit_p (set_jump_crosses, ALLOCNO_REGNO (allocno))
4105 || ira_equiv_no_lvalue_p (ALLOCNO_REGNO (allocno)))
4106 continue;
4107 for (j = 0; j < i; j++)
4108 {
4109 a = spilled_coalesced_allocnos[j];
4110 n = ALLOCNO_COALESCE_DATA (a)->temp;
4111 if (ALLOCNO_COALESCE_DATA (a)->first == a
4112 && ! bitmap_bit_p (set_jump_crosses, ALLOCNO_REGNO (a))
4113 && ! ira_equiv_no_lvalue_p (ALLOCNO_REGNO (a))
4114 && ! slot_coalesced_allocno_live_ranges_intersect_p (allocno, n))
4115 break;
4116 }
4117 if (j >= i)
4118 {
4119 /* No coalescing: set up number for coalesced allocnos
4120 represented by ALLOCNO. */
4121 ALLOCNO_COALESCE_DATA (allocno)->temp = last_coalesced_allocno_num++;
4122 setup_slot_coalesced_allocno_live_ranges (allocno);
4123 }
4124 else
4125 {
4126 allocno_coalesced_p = true;
4127 merged_p = true;
4128 if (internal_flag_ira_verbose > 3 && ira_dump_file != NULL)
4129 fprintf (ira_dump_file,
4130 " Coalescing spilled allocnos a%dr%d->a%dr%d\n",
4131 ALLOCNO_NUM (allocno), ALLOCNO_REGNO (allocno),
4132 ALLOCNO_NUM (a), ALLOCNO_REGNO (a));
4133 ALLOCNO_COALESCE_DATA (allocno)->temp
4134 = ALLOCNO_COALESCE_DATA (a)->temp;
4135 setup_slot_coalesced_allocno_live_ranges (allocno);
4136 merge_allocnos (a, allocno);
4137 ira_assert (ALLOCNO_COALESCE_DATA (a)->first == a);
4138 }
4139 }
4140 for (i = 0; i < ira_allocnos_num; i++)
4141 ira_finish_live_range_list (slot_coalesced_allocnos_live_ranges[i]);
4142 ira_free (slot_coalesced_allocnos_live_ranges);
4143 return merged_p;
4144}
4145
4146/* Sort pseudo-register numbers in array PSEUDO_REGNOS of length N for
4147 subsequent assigning stack slots to them in the reload pass. To do
4148 this we coalesce spilled allocnos first to decrease the number of
4149 memory-memory move insns. This function is called by the
4150 reload. */
4151void
4152ira_sort_regnos_for_alter_reg (int *pseudo_regnos, int n,
4153 unsigned int *reg_max_ref_width)
4154{
4155 int max_regno = max_reg_num ();
4156 int i, regno, num, slot_num;
4157 ira_allocno_t allocno, a;
4158 ira_allocno_iterator ai;
4159 ira_allocno_t *spilled_coalesced_allocnos;
4160
4161 ira_assert (! ira_use_lra_p);
4162
4163 /* Set up allocnos can be coalesced. */
4164 coloring_allocno_bitmap = ira_allocate_bitmap ();
4165 for (i = 0; i < n; i++)
4166 {
4167 regno = pseudo_regnos[i];
4168 allocno = ira_regno_allocno_map[regno];
4169 if (allocno != NULL)
4170 bitmap_set_bit (coloring_allocno_bitmap, ALLOCNO_NUM (allocno));
4171 }
4172 allocno_coalesced_p = false;
4173 processed_coalesced_allocno_bitmap = ira_allocate_bitmap ();
4174 allocno_coalesce_data
4175 = (coalesce_data_t) ira_allocate (sizeof (struct coalesce_data)
4176 * ira_allocnos_num);
4177 /* Initialize coalesce data for allocnos. */
4178 FOR_EACH_ALLOCNO (a, ai)
4179 {
4180 ALLOCNO_ADD_DATA (a) = allocno_coalesce_data + ALLOCNO_NUM (a);
4181 ALLOCNO_COALESCE_DATA (a)->first = a;
4182 ALLOCNO_COALESCE_DATA (a)->next = a;
4183 }
4184 coalesce_allocnos ();
4185 ira_free_bitmap (coloring_allocno_bitmap);
4186 regno_coalesced_allocno_cost
4187 = (int *) ira_allocate (max_regno * sizeof (int));
4188 regno_coalesced_allocno_num
4189 = (int *) ira_allocate (max_regno * sizeof (int));
4190 memset (regno_coalesced_allocno_num, 0, max_regno * sizeof (int));
4191 setup_coalesced_allocno_costs_and_nums (pseudo_regnos, n);
4192 /* Sort regnos according frequencies of the corresponding coalesced
4193 allocno sets. */
4194 qsort (pseudo_regnos, n, sizeof (int), coalesced_pseudo_reg_freq_compare);
4195 spilled_coalesced_allocnos
4196 = (ira_allocno_t *) ira_allocate (ira_allocnos_num
4197 * sizeof (ira_allocno_t));
4198 /* Collect allocnos representing the spilled coalesced allocno
4199 sets. */
4200 num = collect_spilled_coalesced_allocnos (pseudo_regnos, n,
4201 spilled_coalesced_allocnos);
4202 if (flag_ira_share_spill_slots
4203 && coalesce_spill_slots (spilled_coalesced_allocnos, num))
4204 {
4205 setup_coalesced_allocno_costs_and_nums (pseudo_regnos, n);
4206 qsort (pseudo_regnos, n, sizeof (int),
4207 coalesced_pseudo_reg_freq_compare);
4208 num = collect_spilled_coalesced_allocnos (pseudo_regnos, n,
4209 spilled_coalesced_allocnos);
4210 }
4211 ira_free_bitmap (processed_coalesced_allocno_bitmap);
4212 allocno_coalesced_p = false;
4213 /* Assign stack slot numbers to spilled allocno sets, use smaller
4214 numbers for most frequently used coalesced allocnos. -1 is
4215 reserved for dynamic search of stack slots for pseudos spilled by
4216 the reload. */
4217 slot_num = 1;
4218 for (i = 0; i < num; i++)
4219 {
4220 allocno = spilled_coalesced_allocnos[i];
4221 if (ALLOCNO_COALESCE_DATA (allocno)->first != allocno
4222 || ALLOCNO_HARD_REGNO (allocno) >= 0
4223 || ira_equiv_no_lvalue_p (ALLOCNO_REGNO (allocno)))
4224 continue;
4225 if (internal_flag_ira_verbose > 3 && ira_dump_file != NULL)
4226 fprintf (ira_dump_file, " Slot %d (freq,size):", slot_num);
4227 slot_num++;
4228 for (a = ALLOCNO_COALESCE_DATA (allocno)->next;;
4229 a = ALLOCNO_COALESCE_DATA (a)->next)
4230 {
4231 ira_assert (ALLOCNO_HARD_REGNO (a) < 0);
4232 ALLOCNO_HARD_REGNO (a) = -slot_num;
4233 if (internal_flag_ira_verbose > 3 && ira_dump_file != NULL)
4234 fprintf (ira_dump_file, " a%dr%d(%d,%d)",
4235 ALLOCNO_NUM (a), ALLOCNO_REGNO (a), ALLOCNO_FREQ (a),
4236 MAX (PSEUDO_REGNO_BYTES (ALLOCNO_REGNO (a)),
4237 reg_max_ref_width[ALLOCNO_REGNO (a)]));
4238
4239 if (a == allocno)
4240 break;
4241 }
4242 if (internal_flag_ira_verbose > 3 && ira_dump_file != NULL)
4243 fprintf (ira_dump_file, "\n");
4244 }
4245 ira_spilled_reg_stack_slots_num = slot_num - 1;
4246 ira_free (spilled_coalesced_allocnos);
4247 /* Sort regnos according the slot numbers. */
4248 regno_max_ref_width = reg_max_ref_width;
4249 qsort (pseudo_regnos, n, sizeof (int), coalesced_pseudo_reg_slot_compare);
4250 FOR_EACH_ALLOCNO (a, ai)
4251 ALLOCNO_ADD_DATA (a) = NULL;
4252 ira_free (allocno_coalesce_data);
4253 ira_free (regno_coalesced_allocno_num);
4254 ira_free (regno_coalesced_allocno_cost);
4255}

4262/* The function is called from reload to mark changes in the
4263 allocation of REGNO made by the reload. Remember that reg_renumber
4264 reflects the change result. */
4265void
4266ira_mark_allocation_change (int regno)
4267{
4268 ira_allocno_t a = ira_regno_allocno_map[regno];
4269 int old_hard_regno, hard_regno, cost;
4270 enum reg_class aclass = ALLOCNO_CLASS (a);
4271
4272 ira_assert (a != NULL);
4273 hard_regno = reg_renumber[regno];
4274 if ((old_hard_regno = ALLOCNO_HARD_REGNO (a)) == hard_regno)
4275 return;
4276 if (old_hard_regno < 0)
4277 cost = -ALLOCNO_MEMORY_COST (a);
4278 else
4279 {
4280 ira_assert (ira_class_hard_reg_index[aclass][old_hard_regno] >= 0);
4281 cost = -(ALLOCNO_HARD_REG_COSTS (a) == NULL
4282 ? ALLOCNO_CLASS_COST (a)
4283 : ALLOCNO_HARD_REG_COSTS (a)
4284 [ira_class_hard_reg_index[aclass][old_hard_regno]]);
4285 update_costs_from_copies (a, false, false);
4286 }
4287 ira_overall_cost -= cost;
4288 ALLOCNO_HARD_REGNO (a) = hard_regno;
4289 if (hard_regno < 0)
4290 {
4291 ALLOCNO_HARD_REGNO (a) = -1;
4292 cost += ALLOCNO_MEMORY_COST (a);
4293 }
4294 else if (ira_class_hard_reg_index[aclass][hard_regno] >= 0)
4295 {
4296 cost += (ALLOCNO_HARD_REG_COSTS (a) == NULL
4297 ? ALLOCNO_CLASS_COST (a)
4298 : ALLOCNO_HARD_REG_COSTS (a)
4299 [ira_class_hard_reg_index[aclass][hard_regno]]);
4300 update_costs_from_copies (a, true, false);
4301 }
4302 else
4303 /* Reload changed class of the allocno. */
4304 cost = 0;
4305 ira_overall_cost += cost;
4306}

4308/* This function is called when reload deletes memory-memory move. In
4309 this case we marks that the allocation of the corresponding
4310 allocnos should be not changed in future. Otherwise we risk to get
4311 a wrong code. */
4312void
4313ira_mark_memory_move_deletion (int dst_regno, int src_regno)
4314{
4315 ira_allocno_t dst = ira_regno_allocno_map[dst_regno];
4316 ira_allocno_t src = ira_regno_allocno_map[src_regno];
4317
4318 ira_assert (dst != NULL && src != NULL
4319 && ALLOCNO_HARD_REGNO (dst) < 0
4320 && ALLOCNO_HARD_REGNO (src) < 0);
4321 ALLOCNO_DONT_REASSIGN_P (dst) = true;
4322 ALLOCNO_DONT_REASSIGN_P (src) = true;
4323}

4325/* Try to assign a hard register (except for FORBIDDEN_REGS) to
4326 allocno A and return TRUE in the case of success. */
4327static bool
4328allocno_reload_assign (ira_allocno_t a, HARD_REG_SET forbidden_regs)
4329{
4330 int hard_regno;
4331 enum reg_class aclass;
4332 int regno = ALLOCNO_REGNO (a);
4333 HARD_REG_SET saved[2];
4334 int i, n;
4335
4336 n = ALLOCNO_NUM_OBJECTS (a);
4337 for (i = 0; i < n; i++)
4338 {
4339 ira_object_t obj = ALLOCNO_OBJECT (a, i);
4340 COPY_HARD_REG_SET (saved[i], OBJECT_TOTAL_CONFLICT_HARD_REGS (obj));
4341 IOR_HARD_REG_SET (OBJECT_TOTAL_CONFLICT_HARD_REGS (obj), forbidden_regs);
4342 if (! flag_caller_saves && ALLOCNO_CALLS_CROSSED_NUM (a) != 0)
4343 IOR_HARD_REG_SET (OBJECT_TOTAL_CONFLICT_HARD_REGS (obj),
4344 call_used_reg_set);
4345 }
4346 ALLOCNO_ASSIGNED_P (a) = false;
4347 aclass = ALLOCNO_CLASS (a);
4348 update_curr_costs (a);
4349 assign_hard_reg (a, true);
4350 hard_regno = ALLOCNO_HARD_REGNO (a);
4351 reg_renumber[regno] = hard_regno;
4352 if (hard_regno < 0)
4353 ALLOCNO_HARD_REGNO (a) = -1;
4354 else
4355 {
4356 ira_assert (ira_class_hard_reg_index[aclass][hard_regno] >= 0);
4357 ira_overall_cost
4358 -= (ALLOCNO_MEMORY_COST (a)
4359 - (ALLOCNO_HARD_REG_COSTS (a) == NULL
4360 ? ALLOCNO_CLASS_COST (a)
4361 : ALLOCNO_HARD_REG_COSTS (a)[ira_class_hard_reg_index
4362 [aclass][hard_regno]]));
4363 if (ALLOCNO_CALLS_CROSSED_NUM (a) != 0
4364 && ira_hard_reg_set_intersection_p (hard_regno, ALLOCNO_MODE (a),
4365 call_used_reg_set))
4366 {
4367 ira_assert (flag_caller_saves);
4368 caller_save_needed = 1;
4369 }
4370 }
4371
4372 /* If we found a hard register, modify the RTL for the pseudo
4373 register to show the hard register, and mark the pseudo register
4374 live. */
4375 if (reg_renumber[regno] >= 0)
4376 {
4377 if (internal_flag_ira_verbose > 3 && ira_dump_file != NULL)
4378 fprintf (ira_dump_file, ": reassign to %d\n", reg_renumber[regno]);
4379 SET_REGNO (regno_reg_rtx[regno], reg_renumber[regno]);
4380 mark_home_live (regno);
4381 }
4382 else if (internal_flag_ira_verbose > 3 && ira_dump_file != NULL)
4383 fprintf (ira_dump_file, "\n");
4384 for (i = 0; i < n; i++)
4385 {
4386 ira_object_t obj = ALLOCNO_OBJECT (a, i);
4387 COPY_HARD_REG_SET (OBJECT_TOTAL_CONFLICT_HARD_REGS (obj), saved[i]);
4388 }
4389 return reg_renumber[regno] >= 0;
4390}

4392/* Sort pseudos according their usage frequencies (putting most
4393 frequently ones first). */
4394static int
4395pseudo_reg_compare (const void *v1p, const void *v2p)
4396{
4397 int regno1 = *(const int *) v1p;
4398 int regno2 = *(const int *) v2p;
4399 int diff;
4400
4401 if ((diff = REG_FREQ (regno2) - REG_FREQ (regno1)) != 0)
4402 return diff;
4403 return regno1 - regno2;
4404}
4405
4406/* Try to allocate hard registers to SPILLED_PSEUDO_REGS (there are
4407 NUM of them) or spilled pseudos conflicting with pseudos in
4408 SPILLED_PSEUDO_REGS. Return TRUE and update SPILLED, if the
4409 allocation has been changed. The function doesn't use
4410 BAD_SPILL_REGS and hard registers in PSEUDO_FORBIDDEN_REGS and
4411 PSEUDO_PREVIOUS_REGS for the corresponding pseudos. The function
4412 is called by the reload pass at the end of each reload
4413 iteration. */
4414bool
4415ira_reassign_pseudos (int *spilled_pseudo_regs, int num,
4416 HARD_REG_SET bad_spill_regs,
4417 HARD_REG_SET *pseudo_forbidden_regs,
4418 HARD_REG_SET *pseudo_previous_regs,
4419 bitmap spilled)
4420{
4421 int i, n, regno;
4422 bool changed_p;
4423 ira_allocno_t a;
4424 HARD_REG_SET forbidden_regs;
4425 bitmap temp = BITMAP_ALLOC (NULL);
4426
4427 /* Add pseudos which conflict with pseudos already in
4428 SPILLED_PSEUDO_REGS to SPILLED_PSEUDO_REGS. This is preferable
4429 to allocating in two steps as some of the conflicts might have
4430 a higher priority than the pseudos passed in SPILLED_PSEUDO_REGS. */
4431 for (i = 0; i < num; i++)
4432 bitmap_set_bit (temp, spilled_pseudo_regs[i]);
4433
4434 for (i = 0, n = num; i < n; i++)
4435 {
4436 int nr, j;
4437 int regno = spilled_pseudo_regs[i];
4438 bitmap_set_bit (temp, regno);
4439
4440 a = ira_regno_allocno_map[regno];
4441 nr = ALLOCNO_NUM_OBJECTS (a);
4442 for (j = 0; j < nr; j++)
4443 {
4444 ira_object_t conflict_obj;
4445 ira_object_t obj = ALLOCNO_OBJECT (a, j);
4446 ira_object_conflict_iterator oci;
4447
4448 FOR_EACH_OBJECT_CONFLICT (obj, conflict_obj, oci)
4449 {
4450 ira_allocno_t conflict_a = OBJECT_ALLOCNO (conflict_obj);
4451 if (ALLOCNO_HARD_REGNO (conflict_a) < 0
4452 && ! ALLOCNO_DONT_REASSIGN_P (conflict_a)
4453 && bitmap_set_bit (temp, ALLOCNO_REGNO (conflict_a)))
4454 {
4455 spilled_pseudo_regs[num++] = ALLOCNO_REGNO (conflict_a);
4456 /* ?!? This seems wrong. */
4457 bitmap_set_bit (consideration_allocno_bitmap,
4458 ALLOCNO_NUM (conflict_a));
4459 }
4460 }
4461 }
4462 }
4463
4464 if (num > 1)
4465 qsort (spilled_pseudo_regs, num, sizeof (int), pseudo_reg_compare);
4466 changed_p = false;
4467 /* Try to assign hard registers to pseudos from
4468 SPILLED_PSEUDO_REGS. */
4469 for (i = 0; i < num; i++)
4470 {
4471 regno = spilled_pseudo_regs[i];
4472 COPY_HARD_REG_SET (forbidden_regs, bad_spill_regs);
4473 IOR_HARD_REG_SET (forbidden_regs, pseudo_forbidden_regs[regno]);
4474 IOR_HARD_REG_SET (forbidden_regs, pseudo_previous_regs[regno]);
4475 gcc_assert (reg_renumber[regno] < 0);
4476 a = ira_regno_allocno_map[regno];
4477 ira_mark_allocation_change (regno);
4478 ira_assert (reg_renumber[regno] < 0);
4479 if (internal_flag_ira_verbose > 3 && ira_dump_file != NULL)
4480 fprintf (ira_dump_file,
4481 " Try Assign %d(a%d), cost=%d", regno, ALLOCNO_NUM (a),
4482 ALLOCNO_MEMORY_COST (a)
4483 - ALLOCNO_CLASS_COST (a));
4484 allocno_reload_assign (a, forbidden_regs);
4485 if (reg_renumber[regno] >= 0)
4486 {
4487 CLEAR_REGNO_REG_SET (spilled, regno);
4488 changed_p = true;
4489 }
4490 }
4491 BITMAP_FREE (temp);
4492 return changed_p;
4493}

4495/* The function is called by reload and returns already allocated
4496 stack slot (if any) for REGNO with given INHERENT_SIZE and
4497 TOTAL_SIZE. In the case of failure to find a slot which can be
4498 used for REGNO, the function returns NULL. */
4499rtx
4500ira_reuse_stack_slot (int regno, unsigned int inherent_size,
4501 unsigned int total_size)
4502{
4503 unsigned int i;
4504 int slot_num, best_slot_num;
4505 int cost, best_cost;
4506 ira_copy_t cp, next_cp;
4507 ira_allocno_t another_allocno, allocno = ira_regno_allocno_map[regno];
4508 rtx x;
4509 bitmap_iterator bi;
4510 struct ira_spilled_reg_stack_slot *slot = NULL;
4511
4512 ira_assert (! ira_use_lra_p);
4513
4514 ira_assert (inherent_size == PSEUDO_REGNO_BYTES (regno)
4515 && inherent_size <= total_size
4516 && ALLOCNO_HARD_REGNO (allocno) < 0);
4517 if (! flag_ira_share_spill_slots)
4518 return NULL_RTX;
4519 slot_num = -ALLOCNO_HARD_REGNO (allocno) - 2;
4520 if (slot_num != -1)
4521 {
4522 slot = &ira_spilled_reg_stack_slots[slot_num];
4523 x = slot->mem;
4524 }
4525 else
4526 {
4527 best_cost = best_slot_num = -1;
4528 x = NULL_RTX;
4529 /* It means that the pseudo was spilled in the reload pass, try
4530 to reuse a slot. */
4531 for (slot_num = 0;
4532 slot_num < ira_spilled_reg_stack_slots_num;
4533 slot_num++)
4534 {
4535 slot = &ira_spilled_reg_stack_slots[slot_num];
4536 if (slot->mem == NULL_RTX)
4537 continue;
4538 if (slot->width < total_size
4539 || GET_MODE_SIZE (GET_MODE (slot->mem)) < inherent_size)
4540 continue;
4541
4542 EXECUTE_IF_SET_IN_BITMAP (&slot->spilled_regs,
4543 FIRST_PSEUDO_REGISTER, i, bi)
4544 {
4545 another_allocno = ira_regno_allocno_map[i];
4546 if (allocnos_conflict_by_live_ranges_p (allocno,
4547 another_allocno))
4548 goto cont;
4549 }
4550 for (cost = 0, cp = ALLOCNO_COPIES (allocno);
4551 cp != NULL;
4552 cp = next_cp)
4553 {
4554 if (cp->first == allocno)
4555 {
4556 next_cp = cp->next_first_allocno_copy;
4557 another_allocno = cp->second;
4558 }
4559 else if (cp->second == allocno)
4560 {
4561 next_cp = cp->next_second_allocno_copy;
4562 another_allocno = cp->first;
4563 }
4564 else
4565 gcc_unreachable ();
4566 if (cp->insn == NULL_RTX)
4567 continue;
4568 if (bitmap_bit_p (&slot->spilled_regs,
4569 ALLOCNO_REGNO (another_allocno)))
4570 cost += cp->freq;
4571 }
4572 if (cost > best_cost)
4573 {
4574 best_cost = cost;
4575 best_slot_num = slot_num;
4576 }
4577 cont:
4578 ;
4579 }
4580 if (best_cost >= 0)
4581 {
4582 slot_num = best_slot_num;
4583 slot = &ira_spilled_reg_stack_slots[slot_num];
4584 SET_REGNO_REG_SET (&slot->spilled_regs, regno);
4585 x = slot->mem;
4586 ALLOCNO_HARD_REGNO (allocno) = -slot_num - 2;
4587 }
4588 }
4589 if (x != NULL_RTX)
4590 {
4591 ira_assert (slot->width >= total_size);
4592#ifdef ENABLE_IRA_CHECKING
4593 EXECUTE_IF_SET_IN_BITMAP (&slot->spilled_regs,
4594 FIRST_PSEUDO_REGISTER, i, bi)
4595 {
4596 ira_assert (! conflict_by_live_ranges_p (regno, i));
4597 }
4598#endif
4599 SET_REGNO_REG_SET (&slot->spilled_regs, regno);
4600 if (internal_flag_ira_verbose > 3 && ira_dump_file)
4601 {
4602 fprintf (ira_dump_file, " Assigning %d(freq=%d) slot %d of",
4603 regno, REG_FREQ (regno), slot_num);
4604 EXECUTE_IF_SET_IN_BITMAP (&slot->spilled_regs,
4605 FIRST_PSEUDO_REGISTER, i, bi)
4606 {
4607 if ((unsigned) regno != i)
4608 fprintf (ira_dump_file, " %d", i);
4609 }
4610 fprintf (ira_dump_file, "\n");
4611 }
4612 }
4613 return x;
4614}

4616/* This is called by reload every time a new stack slot X with
4617 TOTAL_SIZE was allocated for REGNO. We store this info for
4618 subsequent ira_reuse_stack_slot calls. */
4619void
4620ira_mark_new_stack_slot (rtx x, int regno, unsigned int total_size)
4621{
4622 struct ira_spilled_reg_stack_slot *slot;
4623 int slot_num;
4624 ira_allocno_t allocno;
4625
4626 ira_assert (! ira_use_lra_p);
4627
4628 ira_assert (PSEUDO_REGNO_BYTES (regno) <= total_size);
4629 allocno = ira_regno_allocno_map[regno];
4630 slot_num = -ALLOCNO_HARD_REGNO (allocno) - 2;
4631 if (slot_num == -1)
4632 {
4633 slot_num = ira_spilled_reg_stack_slots_num++;
4634 ALLOCNO_HARD_REGNO (allocno) = -slot_num - 2;
4635 }
4636 slot = &ira_spilled_reg_stack_slots[slot_num];
4637 INIT_REG_SET (&slot->spilled_regs);
4638 SET_REGNO_REG_SET (&slot->spilled_regs, regno);
4639 slot->mem = x;
4640 slot->width = total_size;
4641 if (internal_flag_ira_verbose > 3 && ira_dump_file)
4642 fprintf (ira_dump_file, " Assigning %d(freq=%d) a new slot %d\n",
4643 regno, REG_FREQ (regno), slot_num);
4644}
4645
4646
4647/* Return spill cost for pseudo-registers whose numbers are in array
4648 REGNOS (with a negative number as an end marker) for reload with
4649 given IN and OUT for INSN. Return also number points (through
4650 EXCESS_PRESSURE_LIVE_LENGTH) where the pseudo-register lives and
4651 the register pressure is high, number of references of the
4652 pseudo-registers (through NREFS), number of callee-clobbered
4653 hard-registers occupied by the pseudo-registers (through
4654 CALL_USED_COUNT), and the first hard regno occupied by the
4655 pseudo-registers (through FIRST_HARD_REGNO). */
4656static int
4657calculate_spill_cost (int *regnos, rtx in, rtx out, rtx_insn *insn,
4658 int *excess_pressure_live_length,
4659 int *nrefs, int *call_used_count, int *first_hard_regno)
4660{
4661 int i, cost, regno, hard_regno, j, count, saved_cost, nregs;
4662 bool in_p, out_p;
4663 int length;
4664 ira_allocno_t a;
4665
4666 *nrefs = 0;
4667 for (length = count = cost = i = 0;; i++)
4668 {
4669 regno = regnos[i];
4670 if (regno < 0)
4671 break;
4672 *nrefs += REG_N_REFS (regno);
4673 hard_regno = reg_renumber[regno];
4674 ira_assert (hard_regno >= 0);
4675 a = ira_regno_allocno_map[regno];
4676 length += ALLOCNO_EXCESS_PRESSURE_POINTS_NUM (a) / ALLOCNO_NUM_OBJECTS (a);
4677 cost += ALLOCNO_MEMORY_COST (a) - ALLOCNO_CLASS_COST (a);
4678 nregs = hard_regno_nregs[hard_regno][ALLOCNO_MODE (a)];
4679 for (j = 0; j < nregs; j++)
4680 if (! TEST_HARD_REG_BIT (call_used_reg_set, hard_regno + j))
4681 break;
4682 if (j == nregs)
4683 count++;
4684 in_p = in && REG_P (in) && (int) REGNO (in) == hard_regno;
4685 out_p = out && REG_P (out) && (int) REGNO (out) == hard_regno;
4686 if ((in_p || out_p)
4687 && find_regno_note (insn, REG_DEAD, hard_regno) != NULL_RTX)
4688 {
4689 saved_cost = 0;
4690 if (in_p)
4691 saved_cost += ira_memory_move_cost
4692 [ALLOCNO_MODE (a)][ALLOCNO_CLASS (a)][1];
4693 if (out_p)
4694 saved_cost
4695 += ira_memory_move_cost
4696 [ALLOCNO_MODE (a)][ALLOCNO_CLASS (a)][0];
4697 cost -= REG_FREQ_FROM_BB (BLOCK_FOR_INSN (insn)) * saved_cost;
4698 }
4699 }
4700 *excess_pressure_live_length = length;
4701 *call_used_count = count;
4702 hard_regno = -1;
4703 if (regnos[0] >= 0)
4704 {
4705 hard_regno = reg_renumber[regnos[0]];
4706 }
4707 *first_hard_regno = hard_regno;
4708 return cost;
4709}
4710
4711/* Return TRUE if spilling pseudo-registers whose numbers are in array
4712 REGNOS is better than spilling pseudo-registers with numbers in
4713 OTHER_REGNOS for reload with given IN and OUT for INSN. The
4714 function used by the reload pass to make better register spilling
4715 decisions. */
4716bool
4717ira_better_spill_reload_regno_p (int *regnos, int *other_regnos,
4718 rtx in, rtx out, rtx_insn *insn)
4719{
4720 int cost, other_cost;
4721 int length, other_length;
4722 int nrefs, other_nrefs;
4723 int call_used_count, other_call_used_count;
4724 int hard_regno, other_hard_regno;
4725
4726 cost = calculate_spill_cost (regnos, in, out, insn,
4727 &length, &nrefs, &call_used_count, &hard_regno);
4728 other_cost = calculate_spill_cost (other_regnos, in, out, insn,
4729 &other_length, &other_nrefs,
4730 &other_call_used_count,
4731 &other_hard_regno);
4732 if (nrefs == 0 && other_nrefs != 0)
4733 return true;
4734 if (nrefs != 0 && other_nrefs == 0)
4735 return false;
4736 if (cost != other_cost)
4737 return cost < other_cost;
4738 if (length != other_length)
4739 return length > other_length;
4740#ifdef REG_ALLOC_ORDER
4741 if (hard_regno >= 0 && other_hard_regno >= 0)
4742 return (inv_reg_alloc_order[hard_regno]
4743 < inv_reg_alloc_order[other_hard_regno]);
4744#else
4745 if (call_used_count != other_call_used_count)
4746 return call_used_count > other_call_used_count;
4747#endif
4748 return false;
4749}

4795/* This page contains a simple register allocator without usage of
4796 allocno conflicts. This is used for fast allocation for -O0. */
4797
4798/* Do register allocation by not using allocno conflicts. It uses
4799 only allocno live ranges. The algorithm is close to Chow's
4800 priority coloring. */
4801static void
4802fast_allocation (void)
4803{
4804 int i, j, k, num, class_size, hard_regno;
4805#ifdef STACK_REGS
4806 bool no_stack_reg_p;
4807#endif
4808 enum reg_class aclass;
4809 machine_mode mode;
4810 ira_allocno_t a;
4811 ira_allocno_iterator ai;
4812 live_range_t r;
4813 HARD_REG_SET conflict_hard_regs, *used_hard_regs;
4814
4815 sorted_allocnos = (ira_allocno_t *) ira_allocate (sizeof (ira_allocno_t)
4816 * ira_allocnos_num);
4817 num = 0;
4818 FOR_EACH_ALLOCNO (a, ai)
4819 sorted_allocnos[num++] = a;
4820 allocno_priorities = (int *) ira_allocate (sizeof (int) * ira_allocnos_num);
4821 setup_allocno_priorities (sorted_allocnos, num);
4822 used_hard_regs = (HARD_REG_SET *) ira_allocate (sizeof (HARD_REG_SET)
4823 * ira_max_point);
4824 for (i = 0; i < ira_max_point; i++)
4825 CLEAR_HARD_REG_SET (used_hard_regs[i]);
4826 qsort (sorted_allocnos, num, sizeof (ira_allocno_t),
4827 allocno_priority_compare_func);
4828 for (i = 0; i < num; i++)
4829 {
4830 int nr, l;
4831
4832 a = sorted_allocnos[i];
4833 nr = ALLOCNO_NUM_OBJECTS (a);
4834 CLEAR_HARD_REG_SET (conflict_hard_regs);
4835 for (l = 0; l < nr; l++)
4836 {
4837 ira_object_t obj = ALLOCNO_OBJECT (a, l);
4838 IOR_HARD_REG_SET (conflict_hard_regs,
4839 OBJECT_CONFLICT_HARD_REGS (obj));
4840 for (r = OBJECT_LIVE_RANGES (obj); r != NULL; r = r->next)
4841 for (j = r->start; j <= r->finish; j++)
4842 IOR_HARD_REG_SET (conflict_hard_regs, used_hard_regs[j]);
4843 }
4844 aclass = ALLOCNO_CLASS (a);
4845 ALLOCNO_ASSIGNED_P (a) = true;
4846 ALLOCNO_HARD_REGNO (a) = -1;
4847 if (hard_reg_set_subset_p (reg_class_contents[aclass],
4848 conflict_hard_regs))
4849 continue;
4850 mode = ALLOCNO_MODE (a);
4851#ifdef STACK_REGS
4852 no_stack_reg_p = ALLOCNO_NO_STACK_REG_P (a);
4853#endif
4854 class_size = ira_class_hard_regs_num[aclass];
4855 for (j = 0; j < class_size; j++)
4856 {
4857 hard_regno = ira_class_hard_regs[aclass][j];
4858#ifdef STACK_REGS
4859 if (no_stack_reg_p && FIRST_STACK_REG <= hard_regno
4860 && hard_regno <= LAST_STACK_REG)
4861 continue;
4862#endif
4863 if (ira_hard_reg_set_intersection_p (hard_regno, mode, conflict_hard_regs)
4864 || (TEST_HARD_REG_BIT
4865 (ira_prohibited_class_mode_regs[aclass][mode], hard_regno)))
4866 continue;
4867 ALLOCNO_HARD_REGNO (a) = hard_regno;
4868 for (l = 0; l < nr; l++)
4869 {
4870 ira_object_t obj = ALLOCNO_OBJECT (a, l);
4871 for (r = OBJECT_LIVE_RANGES (obj); r != NULL; r = r->next)
4872 for (k = r->start; k <= r->finish; k++)
4873 IOR_HARD_REG_SET (used_hard_regs[k],
4874 ira_reg_mode_hard_regset[hard_regno][mode]);
4875 }
4876 break;
4877 }
4878 }
4879 ira_free (sorted_allocnos);
4880 ira_free (used_hard_regs);
4881 ira_free (allocno_priorities);
4882 if (internal_flag_ira_verbose > 1 && ira_dump_file != NULL)
4883 ira_print_disposition (ira_dump_file);
4884}

4887
4888/* Entry function doing coloring. */
4889void
4890ira_color (void)
4891{
4892 ira_allocno_t a;
4893 ira_allocno_iterator ai;
4894
4895 /* Setup updated costs. */
4896 FOR_EACH_ALLOCNO (a, ai)
4897 {
4898 ALLOCNO_UPDATED_MEMORY_COST (a) = ALLOCNO_MEMORY_COST (a);
4899 ALLOCNO_UPDATED_CLASS_COST (a) = ALLOCNO_CLASS_COST (a);
4900 }
4901 if (ira_conflicts_p)
4902 color ();
4903 else
4904 fast_allocation ();
4905}
